obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (17862)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 1st July, 1990, vide notification No. S.O. 475(E), dated 12th June, 1990, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17862&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Railways Act, 1989.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (17863)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17863&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "authorised" means authorised by a railway administration;`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) "Authority" means the Rail Land Development Authority constituted under section 4A;]`
  line
  line `(2) "carriage" means the carriage of passengers or goods by a railway administration;`
  line
  line `(3) "Claims Tribunal" means the Railway Claims Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `Railway Claims Tribunal Act, 1987 (54 of 1987);`
  line
  line `(4) "classification" means the classification of commodities made under section 31 for the`
  line `purpose of determining the rates to be charged for carriage of such commodities;`
  line
  line `(5) "class rates" means the rate fixed for a class of commodity in the classification;`
  line
  line `(6) "Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety or the Commissioner of`
  line `Railway Safety appointed under section 5;`
  line
  line `(7) "commodity" means a specific item of goods;`
  line
  line `^2[(7A) competent authority means any person authorised by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification, to perform the functions of the competent authority for such area as may be specified in`
  line `the notification;]`
  line
  line `(8) "consignee"means the person named as consignee in a railway receipt;`
  line
  line `(9) "consignment" means goods entrusted to a railway administration for carriage;`
  line
  line `(10) "consignor" means the person, named in a railway receipt as consignor, by whom or on`
  line `whose behalf goods covered by the railway receipt are entrusted to a railway administration for`
  line carriage;
  line
  line `(11) "demurrage" means the charge levied for the detention of any rolling stock after the expiry`
  line `of free time, if any, allowed for such detention;`
  line
  line `(12) "endorsee" means the person in whose favour an endorsement is made, and in the case of`
  line `successive endorsements, the person in whose favour the last endorsement is made;`
  line
  line `(13) "endorsement" means the signing by the consignee or the endorsee after adding a direction`
  line `on a railway receipt to pass the property in the goods mentioned in such receipt to a specified person;`
  line
  line `(14) "fare" means the charge levied for the carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(15) "ferry" includes a bridge of boats, pontoons or rafts, a swing bridge, a fly-bridge and a`
  line `temporary bridge and the approaches to, and landing places of, a ferry;`
  line
  line `(16) "forwarding note" means the document executed under section 64;`
  line
  line `(17) "freight" means the charge levied for the carriage of goods including transhipment charges,`
  line `if any;`
  line
  line `(18) "General Manager" means the General Manager of a Zonal Railway appointed under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(19) goods includes`
  line
  line `(i) containers, pallets or similar articles of transport used to consolidate goods; and`
  line
  line `(ii) animals;`
  line
  line `(20) "Government railway" means a railway owned by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(21) "in transit", in relation to the carriage of goods by railway, means the period between the`
  line `commencement and the termination of transit of such goods, and unless otherwise previously`
  line determined
  line
  line `(a) transit commences as soon as the railway receipt is issued or the consignment is loaded,`
  line `whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(b) transit terminates on the expiry of the free time allowed for unloading of consignment`
  line `from any rolling stock and where such unloading has been completed within such free time,`
  line `transit terminates on the expiry of the free time allowed, for the removal of the goods from the`
  line `railway premises;`
  line
  line `(22) "level crossing" means an inter-section of a road with lines of rails at the same level;`
  line
  line `(23) "luggage" means the goods of a passenger either carried by him in his charge or entrusted to`
  line `a railway administration for carriage;`
  line
  line `(24) "lump sum rate" means the rate mutually agreed upon between a railway administration and`
  line `a consignor for the carriage of goods and for any service in relation to such carriage;`
  line
  line `(25) "non-Government railway" means a railway other than a Government railway;`
  line
  line `(26) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `^3[(26A) officer authorised means an officer authorised by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 179;]`
  line
  line `(27) "parcel" means goods entrusted to a railway administration for carriage by a passenger or a`
  line `parcel train;`
  line
  line `(28) "pass" means an authority given by the Central Government or a railway administration to a`
  line `person allowing him to travel as a passenger, but does not include a ticket;`
  line
  line `(29) "passenger" means a person travelling with a valid pass or ticket;`
  line
  line `^4[(29A) person interested includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) all persons claiming an interest in compensation to be made on account of the acquisition`
  line `of land under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) tribals and other traditional forest dwellers, who have lost any`
  line `traditional rights recognised under the Scheduled Tribes and Other Traditional Forest Dwellers`
  line `(Recognition of Forest Rights) Act, 2006 (2 of 2007);`
  line
  line `(iii) a person interested in an easement affecting the land; and`
  line
  line `(iv) persons having tenancy rights under the relevant State laws;]`
  line
  line `(30) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(31) "railway" means a railway, or any portion of a railway, for the public carriage of passengers`
  line `or goods, and includes`
  line
  line `(a) all lands within the fences or other boundary marks indicating the limits of the land`
  line `appurtenant to a railway;`
  line
  line `(b) all lines of rails, sidings, or yards, or branches used for the purposes of, or in connection`
  line `with, a railway;`
  line
  line `(c) all electric traction equipments, power supply and distribution installations used for the`
  line `purposes of, or in connection with, a railway;`
  line
  line `(d) all rolling stock, stations, offices, warehouses, wharves, workshops, manufactories, fixed`
  line `plant and machinery, roads and streets, running rooms, rest houses, institutes, hospitals, water`
  line `works and water supply installations, staff dwellings and any other works constructed for the`
  line `purpose of, or in connection with, railway;`
  line
  line `(e) all vehicles which are used on any road for the purposes of traffic of a railway and owned,`
  line `hired or worked by a railway; and`
  line
  line `(f) all ferries, ships, boats and rafts which are used on any canal, river, lake or other navigable`
  line `inland waters for the purposes of the traffic of a railway and owned, hired or worked by a railway`
  line administration,
  line `but does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) a tramway wholly within a municipal area; and`
  line
  line `(ii) lines of rails built in any exhibition ground, fair, park, or any other place solely for the`
  line `purpose of recreation;`
  line
  line `(32) "railway administration", in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) a Government railway, means the General Manager of a Zonal Railway; and`
  line
  line `(b) a non-Government railway, means the person who is the owner or lessee of the railway or`
  line `the person working the railway under an agreement;`
  line
  line `^5[(32A) "railway land" means any land in which a Government railway has any right, title or`
  line interest;]
  line
  line `(33) "railway receipt" means the receipt issued under section 65;`
  line
  line `(34) "railway servant" means any person employed by the Central Government or by a railway`
  line `administration in connection with the service of a railway ^6[including member of the Railway`
  line `Protection Force appointed under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Railway Protection`
  line `Force Act, 1957 (23 of 1957);]`
  line
  line `(35) "rate" includes any fare, freight or any other charge for the carriage of any passenger or`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(36) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Railway Rates Tribunal under this Act;`
  line
  line `(37) "rolling stock" includes locomotives, lenders, carriages, wagons, rail-cars, containers, trucks,`
  line `trolleys and vehicles of all kinds moving on rails;`
  line
  line `^7[(37A) "special railway project" means a project notified as such by the Central Government`
  line `from time to time, for providing national infrastructure for a public purpose in a specified time-frame,`
  line `covering one or more States or the Union territories;]`
  line
  line `(38) "station to station rate" means a special reduced rate applicable to a specific commodity`
  line `booked between specified stations;`
  line
  line `(39) "traffic" includes rolling stock of every description, as well as passengers and goods;`
  line
  line `^8[(40) Tribunal means the Tribunal referred to in section 33;]`
  line
  line `(41) wharfage means the charge levied on goods for not removing them from the railway after`
  line `the expiry of the free time for such removal;`
  line
  line `(42) "Zonal Railway" means a Zonal Railway constituted under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 163, for clause (40) (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
