obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (17864)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 5
  title `Zonal Railways.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17864&sectionno=3&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose of the efficient`
  line `administration of the Government railways, by notification constitute such railways into as many Zonal`
  line `Railways as it may deem fit and specify in such notification the names and headquarters of such Zonal`
  line `Railways and the areas in respect of which they shall exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The Zonal Railway existing immediately before the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `be Zonal Railways constituted under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, declare any unit of the railways engaged in`
  line `research, development, designing, construction or production of rolling stock, its parts or other equipment`
  line `used on a railway, to be a Zonal Railway.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification, abolish any Zonal Railway or constitute any new`
  line `Zonal Railway out of any existing Zonal Railway or Zonal Railways, change the name or headquarters of`
  line `any Zonal Railway or determine the areas in respect of which a Zonal Railway shall exercise jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (17865)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of General Manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17865&sectionno=4&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint`
  line `a person to be the General Manager of a Zonal Railway.`
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence and control of a Zonal Railway shall vest in the General Manager.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (17866)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 7
  title `Establishment of Railway Land Development Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17866&sectionno=4A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Establishment of Railway Land Development Authority.-- The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, establish an authority to be called the Rail Land Development Authority to exercise the`
  line `powers and discharge the functions conferred on it by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (17867)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 8
  title `Composition of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17867&sectionno=4B&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Composition of Authority.-- (1) The Authority shall consist of a Chairman, Vice-Chairman and`
  line `not more than four other members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Member Engineering, Railway Board shall be the Chairman, ex officio, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The Vice-Chairman and three other members shall be appointed by the Central Government from`
  line `amongst persons who are or have been working in the Civil Engineering, Finance and Traffic disciplines`
  line `of any railway administration and having adequate experience in the relevant discipline as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall also appoint a member who shall be a person from outside the`
  line `railway administration and having adequate experience in such field as it may consider necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_c:
  sectionId (17868)
  sectionNo 4C
  orderNo 9
  title `Terms and conditions of appointment of Vice-Chairman and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17868&sectionno=4C&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[4C. Terms and conditions of appointment of Vice-Chairman and other Members.-- The terms`
  line `and conditions of appointment of the Vice-Chairman and the other Members of the Authority, other than`
  line `the Chairman, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among them shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_d:
  sectionId (17869)
  sectionNo 4D
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17869&sectionno=4D&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[4D. Functions of Authority.-- (1) The Authority shall discharge such functions and exercise such`
  line `powers of the Central Government in relation to the development of railway land and as are specifically`
  line `assigned to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the Central`
  line `Government may assign to the Authority all or any of the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) to prepare scheme or schemes for use of railway land in conformity with the provisions of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(ii) to develop railway land for commercial use as may be entrusted by the Central Government`
  line `for the purpose of generating revenue by non-tariff measures;`
  line
  line `(iii) to develop and provide consultancy, construction or management services and undertake`
  line `operation in India in relation to the development of land and property;`
  line
  line `(iv) to carry out any other work or function as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government,`
  line `by order in writing.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_e:
  sectionId (17870)
  sectionNo 4E
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers of Authority to enter into agreements and execute contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17870&sectionno=4E&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[4E. Powers of Authority to enter into agreements and execute contracts.-- Subject to such`
  line `directions as may be given to it by the Central Government, the Authority shall be empowered to enter`
  line `into agreements on behalf of the Central Government and execute contracts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_f:
  sectionId (17871)
  sectionNo 4F
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure of transaction of business of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17871&sectionno=4F&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[4F. Procedure of transaction of business of Authority.-- The Authority shall have power to`
  line `regulate, by means of regulations made by it, its own procedure (including quorum at its meetings) and`
  line `the conduct of all business to be transacted by it, the constitution of Committees and Sub-Committees of`
  line `Members and the delegation to them any of the powers (excluding the power to make regulations under`
  line `this Chapter) and to perform duties of the Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_g:
  sectionId (17872)
  sectionNo 4G
  orderNo 13
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17872&sectionno=4G&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[4G. Appointment of officers and other employees of Authority-- (1) For the purpose of enabling`
  line `it efficiently to discharge its functions under this Act, the Central Government shall provide the Authority`
  line `with such officers and other employees, and the Authority shall, subject to the rules as may be made by`
  line `the Central Government in this behalf, appoint, whether on deputation or otherwise, such number of`
  line `officers and other employees as it may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of the Authority, shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_4_h:
  sectionId (17873)
  sectionNo 4H
  orderNo 14
  title `Salaries, allowances, etc., to be defrayed out of Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17873&sectionno=4H&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[4H. Salaries, allowances, etc., to be defrayed out of Consolidated Fund of India.--The salaries`
  line `and allowances payable to the Vice-Chairman and other Members of the Authority and the administrative`
  line `expenses including the salaries, allowances and pensions payable to the officers and other employees of`
  line `the Authority shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_i:
  sectionId (17874)
  sectionNo 4-I
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17874&sectionno=4-I&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_4_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[4-I. Power of Authority to make regulations.-- (1) The Authority may, with the previous approval`
  line `of the Central Government, make regulations, consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every regulation made by the Authority under this Chapter shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (17875)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 16
  title `Appointment of Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety and Commissioners of Railway Safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17875&sectionno=5&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may appoint a person to be the Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety`
  line `and such other person as it may consider necessary to be the Commissioners of Railway Safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (17876)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duties of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17876&sectionno=6&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect any railway with a view to determine whether it is fit to be opened for the public`
  line `carriage of passengers and report thereon to the Central Government as required by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) make such periodical or other inspections of any railway or of any rolling stock used thereon`
  line `as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) make an inquiry under this Act into the cause of any accident on a railway; and`
  line
  line `(d) discharge such other duties as are conferred on him by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (17877)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17877&sectionno=7&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Central Government, the Commissioner,`
  line `whenever it is necessary so to do for any of the purposes of this Act, may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter upon and inspect any railway or any rolling stock used thereon;`
  line
  line `(b) by order in writing addressed to a railway administration, require the attendance before him of`
  line `any railway servant and to require answers or returns to such inquiries as he thinks fit to make from`
  line `such railway servant or from the railway administration; and`
  line
  line `(c) require the production of any book, document or material object belonging to or in the`
  line `possession or control of any railway administration which appears to him to be necessary to inspect.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (17878)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 19
  title `Commissioner to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17878&sectionno=8&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall be deemed to be a public servant`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (17879)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 20
  title `Facilities to be afforded to Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17879&sectionno=9&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration shall afford to the`
  line `Commissioner all reasonable facilities for the discharge of the duties or for the exercise of the powers`
  line `imposed or conferred on him by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (17880)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 21
  title `Annual report of Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17880&sectionno=10&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety shall prepare in`
  line `each financial year an annual report giving a full account of the activities of the Commissioners during`
  line `the financial year immediately preceding the financial year in which such report is prepared and forward,`
  line `before such date as may be specified by the Central Government, copies thereof to the Central`
  line `Government, and that Government shall cause that report to be laid, as soon as may be, after its receipt`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (17881)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of railway administrations to execute all necessary works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 47 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-8-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17881&sectionno=11&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, but subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `provisions of any law for the acquisition of land for a public purpose or for companies, and subject also,`
  line `in the case of a non-Government railway, to the provisions of any contract between the non-Government`
  line `railway and the Central Government, a railway administration may, for the purposes of constructing or`
  line `maintaining a railway--`
  line
  line `(a) make or construct in or upon, across, under or over any lands, or any streets, hills, valleys,`
  line `roads, railway, tramways, or any rivers, canals, brooks, streams or other waters, or any drains,`
  line `water-pipes, gas-pipes, oil-pipes, sewers, electric supply lines, or telegraph lines, such temporary or`
  line `permanent inclined-planes, bridges, tunnels, culverts, embankments, adequcts, bridges, roads, lines of rail, ways, passages, conduits, drains, piers, cuttings and fences, in-take wells, tube wells, dams, river`
  line `training and protection works as it thinks proper;`
  line
  line `(b) alter the course of any rivers, brooks, streams or other water courses, for the purpose of`
  line `constructing and maintaining tunnels, bridges, passages or other works over or under them and divert`
  line `or alter either temporarily or permanently, the course of any rivers, brooks, streams or other water`
  line `courses or any roads, streets or ways, or raise or sink the level thereof, in order to carry them more`
  line `conveniently over or under or by the side of the railway;`
  line
  line `(c) make drains or conduits into, through or under any lands adjoining the railway for the purpose`
  line `of conveying water from or to the railway;`
  line
  line `(d) erect and construct such houses, warehouses, offices and other buildings, and such yards,`
  line `stations, wharves, engines, machinery apparatus and other works and conveniences as the railway`
  line `administration thinks proper;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) developing any railway land for commercial use;]`
  line
  line `(e) alter, repair or discontinue such buildings, works and conveniences as aforesaid or any of`
  line `them and substitute others in their stead;`
  line
  line `(f) erect, operate, maintain or repair any telegraph and telephone lines in connection with the`
  line `working of the railway;`
  line
  line `(g) erect, operate, maintain or repair any electric traction equipment, power supply and`
  line `distribution installation in connection with the working of the railway; and`
  line
  line `(h) do all other acts necessary for making, maintaining, altering or repairing and using the`
  line railway.
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (17882)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to alter the position of pipe, electric supply line drain or sewer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17882&sectionno=12&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway`
  line `administration may, for the purpose of exercising the powers conferred on it by this Act, alter the position`
  line `of any pipe for the supply of gas, water, oil or compressed air, or the position of any electric supply line,`
  line `drain or sewer:`
  line
  line `Provided that before altering the position of any such pipe, electric supply line, drain or sewer, the`
  line `railway administration shall give a notice indicating the time at which the work of such alteration shall`
  line `commence, to the local authority or other person having control over the pipe, electric supply line, drain`
  line `or sewer.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration shall execute the work referred to in sub-section (1) to the reasonable`
  line `satisfaction of the local authority or the person receiving the notice under the proviso to sub- section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (17883)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 24
  title `Protection for Government property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17883&sectionno=13&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in sections 11 and 12 shall authorise--`
  line
  line `(a) a railway administration of the Government railway to do anything on or to any works, lands`
  line `or buildings vested in, or in the possession of, a State Government without the consent of that`
  line `Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) a railway administration of a non-Government railway to do anything on or to any works,`
  line `lands or buildings vested in, or in the possession of, the Central Government or a State Government,`
  line `without the consent of the Government concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (17884)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 25
  title `Temporary entry upon land to remove obstruction, to repair or to prevent accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17884&sectionno=14&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where in the opinion of a railway administration--`
  line
  line `(a) there is imminent danger that any tree, post or structure may fall on the railway so as to`
  line `obstruct the movement of rolling stock; or`
  line
  line `(b) any tree, post, structure or light obstructs the view of any signal provided for movement of`
  line `rolling stock; or`
  line
  line `(c) any tree, post or structure obstructs any telephone or telegraph line maintained by it,`
  line `it may take such steps as may be necessary to avert such danger or remove such obstruction and submit a`
  line `report thereof to the Central Government in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in the opinion of a railway administration--`
  line
  line `(a) a slip or accident has occurred; or`
  line
  line `(b) there is apprehension of any slip or accident to any cutting, embankment or other work on a`
  line railway,
  line
  line `it may enter upon any lands adjoining the railway and do all such works as may be necessary for the`
  line `purpose of repairing or preventing such slip or accident and submit a report thereof to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, after considering the report under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), in the interest of public safety, by order, direct the railway administration that further`
  line `action under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be stopped or the same shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified in that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (17885)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 26
  title `Payment of amount for damage or loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17885&sectionno=15&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit shall lie against a railway administration`
  line `to recover any amount for any damage or loss caused in the exercise of the powers conferred by any of`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) A railway administration shall pay or tender payment for any damage or loss caused in the`
  line `exercise of the powers conferred by any of the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, and in case of a`
  line `dispute as to the sufficiency of any amount so paid or tendered or as to the persons entitled to receive the`
  line `amount, it shall immediately refer the dispute for the decision of the District Judge of the district and his`
  line `decision thereon shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the railway administration fails to make a reference within sixty days from the`
  line `date of commencement of the dispute, the District Judge may, on an application made to him by the`
  line `person concerned, direct the railway administration to refer the dispute for his decision.`
  line
  line `(3) The reference under sub-section (2) shall be treated as an appeal under section 96 of the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and shall be disposed of accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any amount has been paid as required by sub-section (2), the railway administration shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force, be discharged from all liabilities to`
  line `any person whatsoever in respect of any amount so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (17886)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 27
  title `Accommodation works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17886&sectionno=16&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway administration shall make and maintain the following`
  line `works for the accommodation of the owners and occupiers of lands adjoining the railway, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) such crossings, bridges, culverts and passages over, under or by the sides of, or leading to or`
  line `from, the railway as may, in the opinion of the State Government, be necessary for the purpose of`
  line `making good any interruptions caused by the railway to the use of the lands through which the`
  line `railway is made; and`
  line
  line `(b) all necessary bridges, tunnels, culverts, drains, water sources or other passages, over, under or`
  line `by the sides of the railway, of such dimensions as will, in the opinion of the State Government, be`
  line `sufficient at all times to convey water as freely from or to the lands lying near or affected by the`
  line `railway as it was before the making of the railway or as nearly as possible.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the works specified in sub-section (1) shall be made at`
  line `the cost of the railway administration during or immediately after the laying out or formation of the`
  line `railway over the lands traversed and in such a manner as to cause as little damage or inconvenience as`
  line `possible to persons interested in the lands or affected by the works:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) a railway administration shall not be required to make any administration shall be liable to`
  line `execute any further or additional the working or using of the railway, or to make any accommodation`
  line `works with respect to which the owners or occupiers of the lands have been paid compensation in`
  line `consideration of their not requiring the said works to be made;`
  line
  line `(b) save as hereinafter, in this Chapter, provided, no railway administration shall be liable to`
  line `execute any further or additional accommodation works for the use of the owners or occupiers of the`
  line `lands after the expiration of ten years from the date on which the railway passing through the lands`
  line `was first opened for public traffic;`
  line
  line `(c) where a railway administration has provided suitable accommodation work for the crossing of`
  line `a road or stream and the road or stream is afterwards diverted by the act or neglect of the person`
  line `having the control thereof, the railway administration shall not be compelled to provide any other`
  line `accommodation work for the crossing of such road or stream.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may specify a date for the commencement of any work to be executed`
  line `under sub-section (1) and, if within three months next after that date, the railway administration fails to`
  line `commence the work or having commenced it, fails to proceed diligently to execute it, the Central`
  line `Government shall, on such failure being brought to its notice by the State Government, issue such`
  line `directions to the railway administration as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression lands shall include public roads.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (17887)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of owner, occupier, State Government or local authority to cause additional accommodation works to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17887&sectionno=17&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an owner or occupier of any land affected by a railway`
  line `considers the works made under section 16 to be insufficient for the use of the land, or if the State`
  line `Government or a local authority desires to construct a public road or other work across, under or over a`
  line `railway, such owner or occupier, or, as the case may be, the State Government or the local authority may,`
  line `at any time, require the railway administration to make at the expense of the owner or occupier or of the`
  line `State Government or the local authority, as the case may be, such further accommodation works as are`
  line `considered necessary and are agreed to by the railway administration.`
  line
  line `(2) The accommodation works made under sub-section (1) shall be maintained at the cost of the`
  line `owner or occupier of the land, the State Government or the local authority, at whose request the works`
  line `were made.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any difference of opinion between the railway administration and the owner or`
  line `occupier, the State Government or the local authority, as the case may be, in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) the necessity of such further accommodation works; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenses to be incurred on the construction of such further accommodation works; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the quantum of expenses on the maintenance of such further accommodation works,`
  line
  line `it shall be referred to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (17888)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 29
  title `Fences, gates and bars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17888&sectionno=18&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, within such time as may be specified by`
  line `it or within such further time, as it may grant, require that--`
  line
  line `(a) boundary marks or fences be provided or renewed by a railway administration for a railway or`
  line `any part thereof and for roads constructed in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(b) suitable gates, chains, bars, stiles or hand-rails be erected or renewed by a railway`
  line `administration at level crossings;`
  line
  line `(c) persons be employed by a railway administration to open and shut gates, chains or bars.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (17889)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 30
  title `Overbridges and underbridges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17889&sectionno=19&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a railway administration has constructed lines of`
  line `rails across a public road at the same level, the State Government or the local authority maintaining the`
  line `road, may, at any time, in the interest of public safety, require the railway administration to take the road`
  line `either under or over the railway by means of a bridge or arch with convenient ascents and descents and`
  line `other convenient approaches, instead of crossing the road on the level, or to execute such other works as`
  line `may, in the circumstances of the case, appear to the State Government or the local authority maintaining`
  line `the road to be best adapted for removing or diminishing the danger arising from the level crossing.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration may require the State Government or the local authority, as the case`
  line `may be, as a condition of executing any work under sub-section (1), to undertake to pay the whole of the cost of the work and the expense of maintaining the work, to the railway administration or such`
  line `proportion of the cost and expenses as the Central Government considers just and reasonable.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any difference of opinion between the railway administration and the State`
  line `Government or the local authority, as the case may be, over any of the matters mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1), it shall be referred to the Central Government, whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (17890)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions for safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17890&sectionno=20&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law, the Central Government may, if it is of the opinion that any work undertaken`
  line `or may be undertaken, is likely to alter or impede the natural course of water flow or cause an increase in`
  line `the volume of such flow endangering any cutting, embankment or other work on a railway, issue`
  line `directions in writing to any person, officer or authority responsible for such work to close, regulate or`
  line `prohibit that work.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (17891)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to acquire land, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17891&sectionno=20A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Power to acquire land, etc.-- (1) Where the Central Government is satisfied that for a public`
  line `purpose any land is required for execution of a special railway project, it may, by notification, declare its`
  line `intention to acquire such land.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1), shall give a brief description of the land and of the`
  line `special railway project for which the land is intended to be acquired.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government or the Union territory, as the case may be, shall for the purposes of this`
  line `section, provide the details of the land records to the competent authority, whenever required.`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority shall cause the substance of the notification to be published in two local`
  line `newspapers, one of which shall be in a vernacular language.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b:
  sectionId (17892)
  sectionNo 20B
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to enter for survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17892&sectionno=20B&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[20B. Power to enter for survey, etc.-- On the issue of a notification under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20A, it shall be lawful for any person, authorised by the competent authority in this behalf, to--`
  line
  line `(a) make any inspection, survey, measurement, valuation or enquiry;`
  line
  line `(b) take levels;`
  line
  line `(c) dig or bore into sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(d) set out boundaries and intended lines of work;`
  line
  line `(e) mark such levels, boundaries and lines placing marks and cutting trenches; or`
  line
  line `(f) do such other acts or things as may be considered necessary by the competent authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_c:
  sectionId (17893)
  sectionNo 20C
  orderNo 34
  title `Evaluation of damages during survey, measurement, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17893&sectionno=20C&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[20C. Evaluation of damages during survey, measurement, etc.-- The damages caused while`
  line `carrying out works on land such as survey, digging or boring sub-soil, marking boundaries or cutting`
  line `trenches or clearing away any standing crop, fence or forest or doing such other acts or things which may`
  line `cause damages while acting under section 20B particularly relating to land which is excluded from`
  line `acquisition proceeding, shall be evaluated and compensation shall be paid to the persons having interest in`
  line `that land, within six months from the completion of the said works.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_d:
  sectionId (17894)
  sectionNo 20D
  orderNo 35
  title `Hearing of objections, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17894&sectionno=20D&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[20D. Hearing of objections, etc.-- (1) Any person interested in the land may, within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of publication of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 20A, object to`
  line `the acquisition of land for the purpose mentioned in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Every objection under sub-section, (1), shall be made to the competent authority in writing, and`
  line `shall set out the grounds thereof and the competent authority shall give the objector an opportunity of`
  line `being heard, either in person or by a legal practitioner, and may, after hearing all such objections and after`
  line `making such further enquiry, if any, as the competent authority thinks necessary, by order, either allow or`
  line `disallow the objections.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "legal practitioner" has the same meaning as in`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Advocates Act, 1961(25 of 1961).`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the competent authority under sub-section (2) shall be final]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_e:
  sectionId (17895)
  sectionNo 20E
  orderNo 36
  title `Declaration of acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17895&sectionno=20E&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[20E. Declaration of acquisition.-- (1) Where no objection under sub-section (1) of section 20D has`
  line `been made to the competent authority within the period specified therein or where the competent`
  line `authority has disallowed the objections under sub-section (2) of that section, the competent authority`
  line `shall, as soon as may be, submit a report accordingly to the Central Government and on receipt of such`
  line `report, the Central Government shall declare, by notification, that the land should be acquired for the`
  line `purpose mentioned in sub-section (1) of section 20A.`
  line
  line `(2) On the publication of the declaration under sub-section (1), the land shall vest absolutely in the`
  line `Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in respect of any land, a notification has been published under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20A for its acquisition, but no declaration under sub-section (1) of this section has been published`
  line `within a period of one year from the date of publication of that notification, the said notification shall`
  line `cease to have any effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the said period of one year, the period during which any action or`
  line `proceedings to be taken in pursuance of the notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 20A is`
  line `stayed by an order of a court shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) A declaration made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall not be called in`
  line `question in any court or by any other authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_f:
  sectionId (17896)
  sectionNo 20F
  orderNo 37
  title `Determination of amount payable as compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17896&sectionno=20F&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[20F. Determination of amount payable as compensation.-- (1) Where any land is acquired under`
  line `this Act, there shall be paid an amount which shall be determined by an order of the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority shall make an award under this section within a period of one year from`
  line `the date of the publication of the declaration and if no award is made within that period, the entire`
  line `proceedings for the acquisition of the land shall lapse:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, after the expiry of the period of limitation, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the delay has been caused due to unavoidable circumstances, and for the reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, he may make the award within an extended period of six months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an award is made within the extended period, the entitled person shall, in`
  line `the interest of justice, be paid an additional compensation for the delay in making of the award, every`
  line `month for the period so extended, at the rate of not less than five per cent. of the value of the award, for`
  line `each month of such delay.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the right of user or any right in the nature of an easement on, any land is acquired under`
  line `this Act, there shall be paid an amount to the owner and any other person whose right of enjoyment in that`
  line `land has been affected in any manner whatsoever by reason of such acquisition, an amount calculated at`
  line `ten per cent. of the amount determined under sub-section (1), for that land.`
  line
  line `(4) Before proceeding to determine the amount under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), as the case`
  line `may be, the competent authority shall give a public notice published in two local newspapers, one of`
  line `which shall be in a vernacular language inviting claims from all persons interested in the land to be`
  line acquired.
  line
  line `(5) Such notice shall state the particulars of the land and shall require all persons interested in such`
  line `land to appear in person or by an agent or by a legal practitioner referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 20D, before the competent authority, at a time and place and to state the nature of their respective`
  line `interest in such land.`
  line
  line `(6) If the amount determined by the competent authority under sub-section (1) or as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (3) is not acceptable to either of the parties, the amount shall, on an application by either of`
  line `the parties, be determined by the arbitrator to be appointed by the Central Government in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996`
  line `(26 of 1996) shall apply to every arbitration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) The competent authority or the arbitrator while determining the amount of compensation under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (6), as the case may be, shall take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the market value of the land on the date of publication of the notification under section 20A;`
  line
  line `(b) the damage, if any sustained by the person interested at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, by reason of the severing of such land from other land;`
  line
  line `(c) the damage, if any, sustained by the person interested at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, by reason of the acquisition injuriously affecting his other immovable property in any manner,`
  line `or his earnings;`
  line
  line `(d) if, in consequences of the acquisition of the land, the person interested is compelled to change`
  line `his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses, if any, incidental to such change.`
  line
  line `(9) In addition to the market-value of the land as above provided, the competent authority or the`
  line `arbitrator, as the case may be, shall in every case award a sum of sixty per centum on such market-value,`
  line `in consideration of the compulsory nature of the acquisition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_g:
  sectionId (17897)
  sectionNo 20G
  orderNo 38
  title `Criterion for determination of market-value of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17897&sectionno=20G&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[20G. Criterion for determination of market-value of land.-- (1) The competent authority shall`
  line `adopt the following criteria in assessing and determining the market-value of the land,--`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum land value, if any, specified in the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), for the`
  line `registration of sale deeds in the area, where the land is situated; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the average of the sale price for similar type of land situated in the village or vicinity,`
  line `ascertained from not less than fifty per cent. of the sale deeds registered during the preceding three`
  line `years, where higher price has been paid,`
  line `whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the provisions of sub-section (1) are not applicable for the reason that:`
  line
  line `(i) the land is situated in such area where the transactions in land are restricted by or under any`
  line `other law for the time being in force in that area; or--`
  line
  line `(ii) the registered sale deeds for similar land as mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) are not`
  line `available for the preceding three years; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the minimum land value has not been specified under the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899)`
  line `by the appropriate authority,`
  line `the concerned State Government shall specify the floor price per unit area of the said land based on the`
  line `average higher prices paid for similar type of land situated in the adjoining areas or vicinity, ascertained`
  line `from not less than fifty per cent. of the sale deeds registered during the preceding three years where`
  line `higher price has been paid, and the competent authority may calculate the value of the land accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall, before assessing and determining the market-value of the land`
  line `being acquired under this Act--br`
  line
  line `(a) ascertain the intended land use category of such land; and`
  line
  line `(b) take into account the value of the land of the intended category in the adjoining areas or`
  line vicinity,
  line `for the purpose of determination of the market-value of the land being acquired.`
  line
  line `(4) In determining the market-value of the building and other immovable property or assets attached`
  line `to the land or building which are to be acquired, the competent authority may use the services of a`
  line `competent engineer or any other specialist in the relevant field, as may be considered necessary by the`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The competent authority may, for the purpose of determining the value of trees and plants, use the`
  line `services of experienced persons in the field of agriculture, forestry, horticulture, sericulture, or any other`
  line `field, as may be considered necessary by him.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of assessing the value of the standing crops damaged during the process of land`
  line `acquisition proceedings, the competent authority may utilise the services of experienced persons in the`
  line `field of agriculture as he considers necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_h:
  sectionId (17898)
  sectionNo 20H
  orderNo 39
  title `Deposit and payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17898&sectionno=20H&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[20H. Deposit and payment of amount.-- (1) The amount determined under section 20F shall be`
  line `deposited by the Central Government, in such manner as may be prescribed by that Government, with the`
  line `competent authority before taking possession of the land.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the amount has been deposited under sub-section (1), the competent`
  line `authority shall on behalf of the Central Government pay the amount to the person or persons entitled`
  line thereto.
  line
  line `(3) Where several persons claim to be interested in the amount deposited under sub-section (1), the`
  line `competent authority shall determine the persons who in its opinion are entitled to receive the amount`
  line `payable to each of them.`
  line
  line `(4) If any dispute arises as to the apportionment of the amount or any part thereof or to any person to`
  line `whom the same or any part thereof is payable, the competent authority shall refer the dispute to the`
  line `decision of the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the limits of whose jurisdiction the land`
  line `is situated.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the amount determined under section 20F by the arbitrator is in excess of the amount`
  line `determined by the competent authority, the arbitrator may award interest at nine per cent. per annum on`
  line `such excess amount from the date of taking possession under section 20-I till the date of actual deposit`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(6) Where the amount determined by the arbitrator is in excess of the amount determined by the`
  line `competent authority, the excess amount together with interest, if any, awarded under sub-section (5) shall`
  line `be deposited by the Central Government, in such manner as may be prescribed by that Government, with`
  line `the competent authority and the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (4) shall apply to such deposit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_i:
  sectionId (17899)
  sectionNo 20-I
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to take possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17899&sectionno=20-I&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[20-I Power to take possession.-- (1) Where any land has vested in the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 20E, and the amount determined by the competent authority under section 20F`
  line `with respect to such land has been deposited under sub-section (1) of section 20H with the competent`
  line `authority by the Central Government, the competent authority may, by notice in writing, direct the owner`
  line `as well as any other person who may be in possession of such land to surrender or deliver possession`
  line `thereof the competent authority or any person duly authorised by it in this behalf within a period of sixty`
  line `days of the service of the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person refuses or fails to comply with any direction made under sub-section (1), the`
  line `competent authority shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of any land situated in any area falling within the metropolitan area, to the`
  line `Commissioner of Police;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of any land situated in any area other than the area referred to in clause (a), to the`
  line `Collector of a district,`
  line
  line `and such Commissioner or Collector, as the case may be, shall enforce the surrender of the land, to the`
  line `competent authority or to the person duly authorised by it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_j:
  sectionId (17900)
  sectionNo 20J
  orderNo 41
  title `Right to enter into land where land has vested in Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17900&sectionno=20J&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[20J. Right to enter into land where land has vested in Central Government.-- Where the land has`
  line `vested in the Central Government under section 20E, it shall be lawful for any person authorised by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf, to enter and do other act necessary upon the land for carrying out the`
  line `building, maintenance, management or operation of the special railway project or part thereof or any other`
  line `work connected therewith.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_k:
  sectionId (17901)
  sectionNo 20K
  orderNo 42
  title `Competent authority to have certain powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17901&sectionno=20K&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[20K. Competent authority to have certain powers of civil court.-- The competent authority shall`
  line `have, for the purposes of this Act, all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commission for examination of witnesses.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_l:
  sectionId (17902)
  sectionNo 20L
  orderNo 43
  title `Utilisation of land for the purpose it is acquired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17902&sectionno=20L&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[20L. Utilisation of land for the purpose it is acquired. --(1) The land acquired under this Act shall`
  line `not be transferred to any other purpose except for a public purpose, and after obtaining the prior approval`
  line `of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) When any land or part thereof, acquired under this Act remains unutilised for a period of five`
  line `years from the date of taking over the possession, the same shall return to the Central Government by`
  line reversion.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_m:
  sectionId (17903)
  sectionNo 20M
  orderNo 44
  title `Sharing with landowners the difference in price of a land when transferred for a higher consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17903&sectionno=20M&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[20M. Sharing with landowners the difference in price of a land when transferred for a higher`
  line `consideration. -- Whenever any land acquired under this Act is transferred to any person for a`
  line `consideration, eighty per cent. of the difference in the acquisition cost and the consideration received,`
  line `which in no case shall be less than the acquisition cost, shall be shared amongst the persons from whom`
  line `the lands were acquired or their heirs, in proportion to the value at which the lands were acquired, and for`
  line `the purpose, a separate fund may be maintained which shall be administered by the competent authority in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_n:
  sectionId (17904)
  sectionNo 20N
  orderNo 45
  title `Land Acquisition Act 1 of 1894 not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_n_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17904&sectionno=20N&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[20N. Land Acquisition Act 1 of 1894 not to apply.-- Nothing in the Land Acquisition Act, 1894`
  line `shall apply to an acquisition under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_o:
  sectionId (17905)
  sectionNo 20-O
  orderNo 46
  title `Application of the National Rehabilitation and Resettlement Policy, 2007 to persons affected due to land acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17905&sectionno=20-O&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[20-O. Application of the National Rehabilitation and Resettlement Policy, 2007 to persons`
  line `affected due to land acquisition.-- The provisions of the National Rehabilitation and Resettlement`
  line `Policy, 2007 for project affected families, notified by the Government of India in the Ministry of Rural`
  line `Development vide number F. 26011/4/2007- LRD dated the 31st October, 2007, shall apply in respect of`
  line `acquisition of land by the Central Government under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_p:
  sectionId (17906)
  sectionNo 20P
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17906&sectionno=20P&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_20_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[20P. Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.-- (1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment of arbitrator under sub-section (6) of section 20F;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the amount shall be deposited with the competent authority under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (6) of section 20H;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of maintenance and administration of separate fund for the purposes of`
  line `section 20M.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (17907)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 48
  title `Sanction of the Central Government to the opening of railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17907&sectionno=21&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No railway shall be opened`
  line `for the public carriage of passengers until the Central Government has, by order, sanctioned the opening`
  line `thereof for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (17908)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 49
  title `Formalities to be complied with before giving sanction to the opening of a railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17908&sectionno=22&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government shall, before giving its sanction to the opening of a railway under section 21, obtain a`
  line `report from the Commissioner that--`
  line
  line `(a) he has made a careful inspection of the railway and the rolling stock that may be used thereon;`
  line
  line `(b) the moving and fixed dimensions as laid down by the Central Government have not been`
  line infringed;
  line
  line `(c) the structure of lines of rails, strength of bridges, general structural character of the works and`
  line `the size of, and maximum gross load upon, the axles of any rolling stock, comply with the`
  line `requirements laid down by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) in his opinion, the railway can be opened for the public carriage of passengers without any`
  line `danger to the public using it.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner is of the opinion that the railway cannot be opened without any danger to the`
  line `public using it, he shall, in his report, state the grounds therefor, as also the requirements which, in his`
  line `opinion, are to be complied with before sanction is given by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, after considering the report of the Commissioner, may sanction the`
  line `opening of a railway under section 21 as such or subject to such conditions as may be considered`
  line `necessary by it for the safety of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (17909)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 50
  title `Sections 21 and 22 to apply to the opening of certain works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17909&sectionno=23&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 21`
  line `and 22 shall apply to the opening of the following works if they form part of, or are directly connected`
  line `with, a railway used for the public carriage of passengers and have been constructed subsequent to the`
  line `giving of a report by the Commissioner under section 22, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) opening of additional lines of railway and deviation lines;`
  line
  line `(b) opening of stations, junctions and level crossings;`
  line
  line `(c) re-modelling of yards and re-building of bridges;`
  line
  line `(d) introduction of electric traction; and`
  line
  line `(e) any alteration or reconstruction materially affecting the structural character of any work to`
  line `which the provisions of sections 21 and 22 apply or are extended by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (17910)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 51
  title `Temporary suspension of traffic.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17910&sectionno=24&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `When an accident has occurred on a railway resulting in a`
  line `temporary suspension of traffic, and either the original lines of rails and works have been restored to their`
  line `original standard or a temporary diversion has been laid for the purpose of restoring communication, the`
  line `original lines of rails and works so restored, or the temporary diversion, as the case may be, may, without`
  line `prior inspection by the Commissioner, be opened for the public carriage of passengers, subject to the`
  line `following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the railway servant incharge of the works undertaken by reason of the accident has certified in`
  line `writing that the opening of the restored lines of rails and works, or of the temporary diversion will not`
  line `in his opinion be attended with danger to the public; and`
  line
  line `(b) a notice of the opening of the lines of rails and works or the diversion shall be sent`
  line `immediately to the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (17911)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to close railway opened for the public carriage of passengers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17911&sectionno=25&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Where, after the`
  line `inspection of any railway opened and used for the public carriage of passengers or any rolling stock used`
  line `thereon, the Commissioner is of the opinion that the use of the railway or of any rolling stock will be`
  line `attended with danger to the public using it, the Commissioner shall send a report to the Central`
  line `Government who may thereupon direct that--`
  line
  line `(i) the railway be closed for the public carriage of passengers; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the use of the rolling stock be discontinued; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the railway or the rolling stock may be used for the public carriage of passengers subject to`
  line `such conditions as it may consider necessary for the safety of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (17912)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 53
  title `Re-opening of closed railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17912&sectionno=26&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `When the Central Government has, under section 25, directed`
  line `the closure of a railway or the discontinuance of the use of any rolling stock--`
  line
  line `(a) the railway shall not be re-opened for the public carriage of passengers until it has been`
  line `inspected by the Commissioner and its re-opening is sanctioned in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(b) the rolling stock shall not be used until it has been inspected by the Commissioner and its`
  line `re-use is sanctioned in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (17913)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 54
  title `Use of rolling stock.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17913&sectionno=27&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration may use such rolling stock as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the construction, operation and working of a railway:`
  line
  line `Provided that before using any rolling stock of a design or type different from that already running on`
  line `any section of the railway, the previous sanction of the Central Government shall be obtained for such`
  line `use:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before giving any such sanction, the Central Government shall obtain a report`
  line `from the Commissioner that he has made a careful inspection of the rolling stock and, in his opinion, such`
  line `rolling stock can be used.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (17914)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 55
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17914&sectionno=28&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that any of its`
  line `powers or functions under this Chapter, except section 29, or the rules made thereunder shall, in relation`
  line `to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised`
  line `or discharged also by a Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (17915)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17915&sectionno=29&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the duties of a railway administration and the Commissioner in regard to the opening of a`
  line `railway for the public carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(b) the arrangements to be made for and the formalities to be complied with before opening a`
  line `railway for the public carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(c) for regulating the mode in which, and the speed at which rolling stock used on railways is to`
  line `be moved or propelled; and`
  line
  line `(d) the cases in which and the extent to which the procedure provided in this Chapter may be`
  line `dispensed with.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (17916)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power to fix rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17916&sectionno=30&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to time, by general or special`
  line `order fix, for the carriage of passengers and goods, rates for the whole or any part of the railway and`
  line `different rates may be fixed for different classes of goods and specify in such order the conditions subject`
  line `to which such rates shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by a like order, fix the rates of any other charges incidental to or`
  line `connected with such carriage including demurrage and wharfage for the whole or any part of the railway`
  line `and specify in the order the conditions subject to which such rates shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (17917)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to classify commodities or alter rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17917&sectionno=31&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall have power to--`
  line
  line `(a) classify or reclassify any commodity for the purpose of determining the rates to be charged for`
  line `the carriage of such commodities; and`
  line
  line `(b) increase or reduce the class rates and other charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (17918)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power of railway administration to charge certain rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17918&sectionno=32&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter, a railway administration may, in respect of the carriage of any commodity and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified,--`
  line
  line `(a) quote a station to station rate;`
  line
  line `(b) increase or reduce or cancel, after due notice in the manner determined by the Central`
  line `Government, a station to station rate, not being a station to station rate introduced in compliance with`
  line `an order made by the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(c) withdraw, alter or amend the conditions attached to a station to station rate other than`
  line `conditions introduced in compliance with an order made by the Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(d) charge any lump sum rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (17919)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 60
  title Tribunal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 163, ibid., for section 33 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17919&sectionno=33&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Tribunal.-- The Railway Claims Tribunal established under section 3 of the Railway Claims`
  line `Tribunal Act, 1987 (54 of 1987) shall, on and from the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the`
  line `Finance Act, 2017, be the Tribunal for the purposes of this Act and the said Tribunal shall exercise the`
  line `jurisdiction, authority and powers conferred on it by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (17920)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 61
  title [Omitted.].
  content `34. [Staff of the Tribunal.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), s. 163 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17920&sectionno=34&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (17921)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 62
  title [Omitted.].
  content `35. [Sittings of the Tribunal.] Omitted by s. 163, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17921&sectionno=35&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (17922)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 63
  title `Complaints against a railway administration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17922&sectionno=36&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any complaint that a railway administration--`
  line
  line `(a) is contravening the provisions of section 70; or`
  line
  line `(b) is charging for the carriage of any commodity between two stations a rate which is`
  line `unreasonable; or`
  line
  line `(c) is levying any other charge which is unreasonable,`
  line
  line `may be made to the Tribunal, and the Tribunal shall hear and decide any such complaint in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (17923)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 64
  title `Matters not within the jurisdiction of the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17923&sectionno=37&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall confer`
  line `jurisdiction on the Tribunal in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) classification or re-classification of any commodity;`
  line
  line `(b) fixation of wharfage and demurrage charges (including conditions attached to such charges);`
  line
  line `(c) fixation of fares levied for the carriage of passengers and freight levied for the carriage of`
  line `luggage, parcels, railway material and military traffic; and`
  line
  line `(d) fixation of lump sum rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (17924)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 65
  title `Powers of the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17924&sectionno=38&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall have the powers of a civil court under the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the purposes of taking evidence on oath, enforcing the attendance`
  line `of witnesses, compelling the discovery and production of documents, issuing commissions for the`
  line `examination of witnesses and of review and shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of`
  line `section 195 and Chapter XXXV of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974) and any reference in such section or chapter to the presiding officer of a court shall be deemed`
  line `to include a reference to the Chairman of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall also have power to pass such interim and final orders as the circumstances may`
  line `require, including orders for the payment of costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (17925)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 66
  title `Reference to the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17925&sectionno=39&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 37, the Central`
  line `Government may make a reference to the Tribunal in respect of any of the matter specified in that section and where any such reference is made in respect of any such matter, the Tribunal shall make an inquiry`
  line `into that matter and submit its report thereon to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (17926)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 67
  title `Assistance by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17926&sectionno=40&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall give to the`
  line `Tribunal such assistance as it may require and shall also place at its disposal any information in the`
  line `possession of the Central Government which that Government may think relevant to any matter before the`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) Any person duly authorised in this behalf by the Central Government shall be entitled to appear`
  line `and be heard in any proceedings before the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (17927)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 68
  title `Burden of proof, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17927&sectionno=41&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `In the case of any complaint under clause (a) of section 36,--`
  line
  line `(a) whenever it is shown that a railway administration charges one trader or class of traders or the`
  line `traders in any local area, lower rates for the same or similar goods or lower charges for the same or`
  line `similar services than it charges to other traders in any other local area, the burden of providing that`
  line `such lower rate or charge does not amount to an undue preference, shall lie on the railway`
  line administration;
  line
  line `(b) in deciding whether a lower rate or charge does not amount to an undue preference, the`
  line `Tribunal may, in addition to any other considerations affecting the case, take into consideration`
  line `whether such lower rate or charge is necessary in the interests of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (17928)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 69
  title `Decision, etc., of the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17928&sectionno=42&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The decisions or orders of the Tribunal shall be by a majority`
  line `of the members sitting and shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (17929)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 70
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17929&sectionno=43&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be instituted or proceeding taken in respect of any`
  line `matter which the Tribunal is empowered to deal with, or decide, under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (17930)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 71
  title `Reliefs which the Tribunal may grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17930&sectionno=44&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `In the case of any complaint made under clause (b) or`
  line `clause (c) of section 36, the Tribunal may--`
  line
  line `(i) fix such rate or charge as it considers reasonable from any date as it may deem proper, not`
  line `being a date earlier to the date of the filing of the complaint;`
  line
  line `(ii) direct a refund of amount, if any, as being the excess of the rate or charge fixed by the`
  line `Tribunal under clause (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (17931)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 72
  title `Revision of decisions given by the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17931&sectionno=45&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where a railway administration considers that`
  line `since the date of decision by the Tribunal, there has been a material change in the circumstances on which`
  line `it was based, it may, after the expiry of one year from such date, make an application to the Tribunal and`
  line `the Tribunal may, after making such inquiry as it considers necessary, vary or revoke the decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (17932)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 73
  title `Execution of decisions or orders of the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17932&sectionno=46&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal may transmit any decision or`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the decision or`
  line `order as if it were a decree made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (17933)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 74
  title `Report to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17933&sectionno=47&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal shall present annually a report to the Central`
  line `Government of all its proceedings under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (17934)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power of the Tribunal to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s.163 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17934&sectionno=48&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, with the previous approval`
  line `of the Central Government, make regulations consistent with this Act and rules generally to regulate its`
  line `procedure for the effective discharge of its functions under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) the award of costs by the Tribunal in any proceedings before it;`
  line
  line `(c) the reference of any question to a member or to an officer of the Tribunal or any other person`
  line `appointed by the Tribunal, for report after holding a local inquiry;`
  line
  line `(d) the right of audience before the Tribunal, provided that any party shall be entitled to be heard`
  line `in person, or by a representative duly authorised in writing, or by a legal practitioner;`
  line
  line `(e) the disposal by the Tribunal of any proceedings before it, notwithstanding that in the course`
  line `thereof there has been a change in the persons sitting as members of the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) a scale of fees for and in connection with the proceedings before the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (17935)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 76
  title `Exhibition of certain timings and tables of fares at stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17935&sectionno=49&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every railway administration`
  line `shall cause to be pasted in a conspicuous and accessible place at every station in Hindi and English and`
  line `also in the regional language commonly in use in the area where the station is situated,--`
  line
  line `(i) a table of times of arrival and departure of trains which carry passengers and stop at that`
  line `station; and`
  line
  line `(ii) list of fares from such station to such other stations as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) At every station where tickets are issued to passengers, a copy of the time table in force shall be`
  line `kept in the office of the station master.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (17936)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 77
  title `Supply of tickets on payment of fare.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17936&sectionno=50&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desirous of travelling on a railway shall,`
  line `upon payment of the fare, be supplied with a ticket by a railway servant or an agent authorised in this`
  line `behalf and such ticket shall contain the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the date of issue;`
  line
  line `(ii) the class of carriage;`
  line
  line `(iii) the place from and the place to which it is issued; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the amount of the fare.`
  line
  line `(2) Every railway administration shall display the hours during which booking windows at a station`
  line `shall be kept open for the issue of tickets to passengers.`
  line
  line `(3) The particulars required to be specified on a ticket under clauses (ii) and (iii) of sub-section (1)`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is for the lowest class of carriage, be set forth in Hindi, English and the regional language`
  line `commonly in use at the place of issue of the ticket; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it is for any other class of carriage, be set forth in Hindi and English:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not feasible to specify such particulars in any such language due to`
  line `mechanisation or any other reason, the Central Government may exempt such particulars being specified`
  line `in that language.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (17937)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 78
  title `Provision for case in which ticket is issued for class or train not having accommodation for additional passengers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17937&sectionno=51&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) A ticket shall be deemed to have been issued subject to the condition of`
  line `availability of accommodation in the class of carriage and the train for which the ticket is issued.`
  line
  line `(2) If no accommodation is available in the class of carriage for which a ticket is issued, and the`
  line `holder thereof travels in a carriage of a lower class, he shall, on returning such ticket, be entitled to a`
  line `refund of the difference between the fare paid by him and the fare payable for the class of carriage in`
  line `which he travels.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (17938)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 79
  title `Cancellation of ticket and refund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17938&sectionno=52&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If a ticket is returned for cancellation, the railway`
  line `administration shall cancel the same and refund such amount as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (17939)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 80
  title `Prohibition against transfer of certain tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17939&sectionno=53&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A ticket issued in the name of a person shall be`
  line `used only by that person:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall prevent mutual transfer of a seat or berth by`
  line `passengers travelling by the same train:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a railway servant authorised in this behalf may permit change of name of a`
  line `passenger having reserved a seat or berth subject to such circumstances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (17940)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 81
  title `Exhibition and surrender of passes and tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17940&sectionno=54&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Every passenger shall, on demand by any`
  line `railway servant authorised in this behalf, present his pass or ticket to such railway servant for examination`
  line `during the journey or at the end of the journey and surrender such ticket--`
  line
  line `(a) at the end of the journey, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such ticket is issued for a specified period, on the expiration of such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (17941)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 82
  title `Prohibition against travelling without pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17941&sectionno=55&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall enter or remain in`
  line `any carriage on a railway for the purpose of travelling therein as a passenger unless he has with him a`
  line `proper pass or ticket or obtained permission of a railway servant authorised in this behalf for such travel.`
  line
  line `(2) A person obtaining permission under sub-section (1) shall ordinarily get a certificate from the`
  line `railway servant referred to in that sub-section that he has been permitted to travel in such carriage on`
  line `condition that he subsequently pays the fare payable for the distance to be travelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (17942)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to refuse to carry persons suffering from infectious or contagious diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17942&sectionno=56&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `person suffering from such infectious or contagious diseases, as may be prescribed, shall not enter or`
  line `remain in any carriage on a railway or travel in a train without the permission of a railway servant`
  line `authorised in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway servant giving permission under sub-section (1), shall arrange for the separation of`
  line `the person suffering from such disease from other persons in the train and such person shall be carried in`
  line `the train subject to such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who enters or remains in any carriage or travels in a train without permission as`
  line `required under sub-section (1) or in contravention of any condition prescribed under sub-section (2), such`
  line `person and a person accompanying him shall be liable to the forfeiture of their passes or tickets and`
  line `removal from railway by any railway servant.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (17943)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 84
  title `Maximum number of passengers for each compartment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17943&sectionno=57&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the approval of the`
  line `Central Government, every railway administration shall fix the maximum number of passengers which`
  line `may be carried in each compartment of every description of carriage, and shall exhibit the number so`
  line `fixed in a conspicuous manner inside or outside each compartment in Hindi, English and also in one or`
  line `more of the regional languages commonly in use in the areas served by the railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (17944)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 85
  title `Earmarking of compartment, etc., for ladies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17944&sectionno=58&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Every railway administration shall, in every`
  line `train carrying passengers, earmark for the exclusive use of females, one compartment or such number of`
  line `berths or seats, as the railway administration may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (17945)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 86
  title `Communications between passengers and railway servant in charge of train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17945&sectionno=59&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `A railway`
  line `administration shall provide and maintain in every train carrying passengers, such efficient means of`
  line `communication between the passengers and the railway servant in charge of the train as may be approved`
  line `by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the railway administration is satisfied that the means of communication provided`
  line `in a train are being misused, it may cause such means to be disconnected in that train for such period as it`
  line `thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may specify the circumstances under which a railway`
  line `administration may be exempted from providing such means of communication in any train.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (17946)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17946&sectionno=60&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the convenience and accommodation (including the reservation of seats or berths in trains) to`
  line passengers;
  line
  line `(b) the amount of refund for the cancellation of a ticket;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances under which change of names of passengers, having reserved seats or`
  line `berths, may be permitted;`
  line
  line `(d) the carriage of luggage and the conditions subject to which luggage may be kept in the cloak`
  line `rooms at the stations;`
  line
  line `(e) diseases which are infectious or contagious;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions subject to which a railway administration may carry passengers suffering from`
  line `infectious or contagious diseases and the manner in which carriages used by such passengers may be`
  line disinfected;
  line
  line `(g) generally, for regulating the travelling upon, and the use, working and management of the`
  line railways.
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this section may provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which shall not exceed five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Every railway administration shall keep at every station on its railway a copy of all the rules made`
  line `under this section and shall also allow any person to inspect it free of charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (17947)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 88
  title `Maintenance of rate-books, etc., for carriage of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17947&sectionno=61&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Every railway administration shall`
  line `maintain, at each station and at such other places where goods are received for carriage, the rate-books or`
  line `other documents which shall contain the rate authorised for the carriage of goods from one station to`
  line `another and make them available for the reference of any person during all reasonable hours without`
  line `payment of any fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (17948)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 89
  title `Conditions for receiving, etc., of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17948&sectionno=62&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway administration may impose conditions,`
  line `not inconsistent with this Act or any rules made thereunder, with respect to the receiving, forwarding,`
  line `carrying or delivering of any goods.`
  line
  line `(2) A railway administration shall maintain, at each station and at such other places where goods are`
  line `received for carriage, a copy of the conditions for the time being in force under sub-section (1) and make`
  line `them available for the reference of any person during all reasonable hours without payment of any fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (17949)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 90
  title `Provisions of risk rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17949&sectionno=63&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any goods are entrusted to a railway administration for`
  line `carriage, such carriage shall, except where owner's risk rate is applicable in respect of such goods, be at`
  line `railway risk rate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any goods, for which owner's risk rate and railway risk rate are in force, may be entrusted for`
  line `carriage at either of the rates and if no rate is opted, the goods shall be deemed to have been entrusted at`
  line `owner's risk rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (17950)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 91
  title `Forwarding note.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17950&sectionno=64&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person entrusting any goods to a railway administration for`
  line `carriage shall execute a forwarding note in such form as may be specified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no forwarding note shall be executed in the case of such goods as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The consignor shall be responsible for the correctness of the particulars furnished by him in the`
  line `forwarding note.`
  line
  line `(3) The consignor shall indemnify the railway administration against any damage suffered by it by`
  line `reason of the incorrectness or incompleteness of the particulars in the forwarding note.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (17951)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 92
  title `Railway receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17951&sectionno=65&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway administration shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the goods are to be loaded by a person entrusting such goods, on the`
  line `completion of such loading; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, on the acceptance of the goods by it, issue a railway receipt in such form as`
  line `may be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A railway receipt shall be prima facie evidence of the weight and the number of packages stated`
  line `therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a consignment in wagon-load or train-load and the weight or the number`
  line `of packages is not checked by a railway servant authorised in this behalf, and a statement to that effect is`
  line `recorded in such railway receipt by him, the burden of proving the weight or, as the case may be, the`
  line `number of packages stated therein, shall lie on the consignor, the consignee or the endorsee.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (17952)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 93
  title `Power to require statement relating to the description of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17952&sectionno=66&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or a person`
  line `having charge of any goods which are brought upon a railway for the purposes of carriage by railway, and`
  line `the consignee or the endorsee of any consignment shall, on the request of any railway servant authorised`
  line `in this behalf, deliver to such railway servant a statement in writing signed by such owner or person or by`
  line `such consignee or endorsee, as the case may be, containing such description of the goods as would enable`
  line `the railway servant to determine the rate for such carriage.`
  line
  line `(2) If such owner or person refuses or neglects to give the statement as required under sub-section (1)`
  line `and refuses to open the package containing the goods, if so required by the railway servant, it shall be`
  line `open to the railway administration to refuse to accept such goods for carriage unless such owner or person`
  line `pays for such carriage the highest rate for any class of goods.`
  line
  line `(3) If the consignee or endorsee refuses or neglects to give the statement as required under`
  line `sub-section (1) and refuses to open the package containing the goods, if so required by the railway`
  line `servant, it shall be open to the railway administration to charge in respect of the carriage of the goods the`
  line `highest rate for any class of goods.`
  line
  line `(4) If the statement delivered under sub-section (1) is materially false with respect to the description`
  line `of any goods to which it purports to relate, the railway administration may charge in respect of the`
  line `carriage of such goods such rate, not exceeding double the highest rate for any class of goods as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) If any difference arises between a railway servant and such owner or person, the consignee or the`
  line `endorsee, as the case may be, in respect of the description of the goods for which a statement has been`
  line `delivered under sub-section (1), the railway servant may detain and examine the goods.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any goods have been detained under sub-section (5) for examination and upon such`
  line `examination it is found that the description of the goods is different from that given in the statement`
  line `delivered under sub-section (1), the cost of such detention and examination shall be borne by such owner`
  line `or person, the consignee or the endorsee, as the case may be, and the railway administration shall not be`
  line `liable for any loss, damage or deterioration which may be caused by such detention or examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (17953)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 94
  title `Carriage of dangerous or offensive goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17953&sectionno=67&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall take with him on a railway, or`
  line `require a railway administration to carry such dangerous or offensive goods, as may be prescribed, except`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall take with him on a railway the goods referred to in sub-section (1) unless he gives`
  line `a notice in writing of their dangerous or offensive nature to the railway servant authorised in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall entrust the goods referred to in sub-section (1) to a railway servant authorised in`
  line `this behalf for carriage unless he distinctly marks on the outside of the package containing such goods`
  line `their dangerous or offensive nature and gives a notice in writing of their dangerous or offensive nature to`
  line `such railway servant.`
  line
  line `(4) If any railway servant has reason to believe that goods contained in a package are dangerous or`
  line `offensive and notice as required under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the case may be, in respect of such goods is not given, he may cause such package to be opened for the purpose of ascertaining its`
  line contents.
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any railway servant may refuse to accept any`
  line `dangerous or offensive goods for carriage or stop, in transit, such goods or cause the same to be removed,`
  line `as the case may be, if he has reason to believe that the provisions of this section for such carriage are not`
  line `complied with.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall be construed to derogate from the provisions of the Indian Explosives`
  line `Act, 1884 (4 of 1884), or any rule or order made under that Act, and nothing in sub-sections (4) and (5)`
  line `shall be construed to apply to any goods entrusted for carriage by order or on behalf of the Government or`
  line `to any goods which a soldier, sailor, airman or any other officer of the armed forces of the Union or a`
  line `police officer or a member of the Territorial Army or of the National Cadet Corps may take with him on a`
  line `railway in the course of his employment or duty as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (17954)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 95
  title `Carriage of animals suffering from infectious or contagious diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17954&sectionno=68&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `A railway`
  line `administration shall not be bound to carry any animal suffering from such infectious or contagious disease`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (17955)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 96
  title `Deviation of route.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17955&sectionno=69&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Where due to any cause beyond the control of a railway administration or`
  line `due to congestion in the yard or any other operational reasons, goods are carried over a route other than`
  line `the route by which such goods are booked, the railway administration shall not be deemed to have`
  line `committed a breach of the contract of carriage by reason only of the deviation of the route.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (17956)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 97
  title `Prohibition of undue preference.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17956&sectionno=70&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration shall not make or give any undue`
  line `or unreasonable preference or advantage to, or in favour of, any particular person or any particular`
  line `description of traffic in the carriage of goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (17957)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to give direction in regard to carriage of certain goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17957&sectionno=71&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, if it is of the opinion that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, by general or special order,`
  line `direct any railway administration--`
  line
  line `(a) to give special facilities for, or preference to, the carriage of such goods or class of goods`
  line `consigned by or to the Central Government or the Government of any State or of such other goods or`
  line `class of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) to carry any goods or class of goods by such route or routes and at such rates;`
  line
  line `(c) to restrict or refuse acceptance of such goods or class of goods at or to such station for`
  line carriage,
  line `as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under sub-section (1) shall cease to have effect after the expiration of a period of`
  line `one year from the date of such order, but may, by a like order, be renewed from time to time for such`
  line `period not exceeding one year at a time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, every railway administration shall be bound to`
  line `comply with any order given under sub-section (1) and any action taken by a railway administration in`
  line `pursuance of any such order shall not be deemed to be a contravention of section 70.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (17958)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 99
  title `Maximum carrying capacity for wagons and trucks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17958&sectionno=72&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The gross weight of every wagon or`
  line `truck bearing on the axles when the wagon or truck is loaded to its maximum carrying capacity shall not`
  line `exceed such limit as may be fixed by the Central Government for the class of axle under the wagon or`
  line truck.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the limit fixed under sub-section (1), every railway administration shall determine the`
  line `normal carrying capacity for every wagon or truck in its possession and shall exhibit in words and figures`
  line `the normal carrying capacity so determined in a conspicuous manner on the outside of every such wagon`
  line `or truck.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person owning a wagon or truck which passes over a railway shall determine and exhibit`
  line `the normal carrying capacity for the wagon or truck in the manner specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), where a railway`
  line `administration considers it necessary or expedient so to do in respect of any wagon or truck carrying any`
  line `specified class of goods or any class of wagons or trucks of any specified type, it may vary the normal`
  line `carrying capacity for such wagon or truck or such class of wagons or trucks and subject to such conditions`
  line `as it may think fit to impose, determine for the wagon or truck or class of wagons or trucks such carrying`
  line `capacity as may be specified in the notification and it shall not be necessary to exhibit the words and`
  line `figures representing the carrying capacity so determined on the outside of such wagon or truck or such`
  line `class of wagons or trucks.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (17959)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 100
  title `Punitive charge for overloading a wagon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17959&sectionno=73&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Where a person loads goods in a wagon beyond its`
  line `permissible carrying capacity as exhibited under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), or notified under`
  line `sub-section (4), of section 72, a railway administration may, in addition to the freight and other charges,`
  line `recover from the consignor, the consignee or the endorsee, as the case may be, charges by way of penalty`
  line `at such rates, as may be prescribed, before the delivery of the goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for the railway administration to unload the goods loaded beyond the`
  line `capacity of the wagon, if detected at the forwarding station or at any place before the destination station and to recover the cost of such unloading and any charge for the detention of any wagon on this account.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (17960)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 101
  title `Passing of property in the goods covered by railway receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17960&sectionno=74&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The property in the`
  line `consignment covered by a railway receipt shall pass to the consignee or the endorsee, as the case may be,`
  line `on the delivery of such railway receipt to him and he shall have all the rights and liabilities of the`
  line consignor.
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (17961)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 102
  title `Section 74 not to affect right of stoppage in transit or claims for freight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17961&sectionno=75&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained`
  line `in section 74 shall prejudice or affect--`
  line
  line `(a) any right of the consignor for stoppage of goods in transit as an unpaid vendor (as defined`
  line `under the Sale of Goods Act, 1930 3 of 1930 ) on his written request to the railway administration;`
  line
  line `(b) any right of the railway to claim freight from the consignor; or`
  line
  line `(c) any liability of the consignee or the endorsee, referred to in that section, by reason of his being`
  line `such consignee or endorsee.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (17962)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 103
  title `Surrender of railway receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17962&sectionno=76&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The railway administration shall deliver the consignment under`
  line `a railway receipt on the surrender of such railway receipt:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the railway receipt is not forthcoming, the consignment may be delivered to the`
  line `person, entitled in the opinion of the railway administration to receive the goods, in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (17963)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power of railway administration to deliver goods or sale proceeds thereof in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17963&sectionno=77&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Where no railway receipt is forthcoming and any consignment or the sale proceeds of any consignment`
  line `are claimed by two or more persons, the railway administration may withhold delivery of such`
  line `consignment or sale proceeds, as the case may be, and shall deliver such consignment or sale proceeds in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (17964)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 105
  title `Power to measure, weigh, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17964&sectionno=78&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the railway receipt, the`
  line `railway administration may, before the delivery of the consignment, have the right to--`
  line
  line `(i) re-measure, re-weigh or re-classify any consignment;`
  line
  line `(ii) re-calculate the freight and other charges; and`
  line
  line `(iii) correct any other error or collect any amount that may have been omitted to be charged.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (17965)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 106
  title `Weighment of consignment on request of the consignee or endorsee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17965&sectionno=79&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `A railway`
  line `administration may, on the request made by the consignee or endorsee, allow weighment of the`
  line `consignment subject to such conditions and on payment of such charges as may be prescribed and the`
  line `demurrage charges if any:`
  line
  line `Provided that except in cases where a railway servant authorised in this behalf considers it necessary`
  line `so to do, no weighment shall be allowed of goods booked at owners risk rate or goods which are`
  line `perishable and are likely to lose weight in transit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no request for weighment of consignment in wagon-load or train-load shall be`
  line `allowed if the weighment is not feasible due to congestion in the yard or such other circumstances as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (17966)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 107
  title `Liability of railway administration for wrong delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17966&sectionno=80&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Where a railway administration`
  line `delivers the consignment to the person who produces the railway receipt, it shall not be responsible for`
  line `any wrong delivery on the ground that such person is not entitled thereto or that the endorsement on the`
  line `railway receipt is forged or otherwise defective.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (17967)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 108
  title `Open delivery of consigrments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17967&sectionno=81&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Where the consignment arrives in a damaged condition or`
  line `shows signs of having been tampered with and the consignee or the endorsee demands open delivery, the`
  line `railway administration shall give open delivery in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (17968)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 109
  title `Partial delivery of consignments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17968&sectionno=82&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The consignee or endorsee shall, as soon as the`
  line `consignment or part thereof is ready for delivery, take delivery of such consignment or part thereof`
  line `notwithstanding that such consignment or part thereof is damaged`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of partial delivery under sub-section (1), the railway administration shall furnish a`
  line `partial delivery certificate, in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the consignee or endorsee refuses to take delivery under sub-section (1), the consignment or`
  line `part thereof shall be subject to wharfage charges beyond the time allowed for removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (17969)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 110
  title `Lien for freight or any other sum due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17969&sectionno=83&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the consignor, the consignee or the endorsee fails`
  line `to pay on demand any freight or other charges due from him in respect of any consignment, the railway`
  line `administration may detain such consignment or part thereof or, if such consignment is delivered, it may`
  line `detain any other consignment of such person which is in, or thereafter comes into its possession.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration may, if the consignment detained under sub-section (1) is--`
  line
  line `(a) perishable in nature, sell at once; or`
  line
  line `(b) not perishable in nature, sell, by public auction,`
  line `such consignment or part thereof, as may be necessary to realise a sum equal to the freight or other`
  line `charges:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a railway administration for reasons to be recorded in writing is of the opinion`
  line `that it is not expedient to hold the auction, such consignment or part thereof may be sold in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The railway administration shall give a notice of not less than seven days of the public auction`
  line `under clause (b) of sub-section (2) in one or more local newspapers or where there are no such`
  line `newspapers in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The railway administration may, out of the sale proceeds received under sub-section (2), retain a`
  line `sum equal to the freight and other charges including expenses for the sale due to it and the surplus of such`
  line `proceeds and the part of the consignment, if any, shall be rendered to the person entitled thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (17970)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 111
  title `Unclaimed consignment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17970&sectionno=84&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person fails to take delivery of`
  line
  line `(a) any consignment; or`
  line
  line `(b) the consignment released from detention made under sub-section (1) of section 83; or`
  line
  line `(c) any remaining part of the consignment under sub-section (2) of section 83,`
  line `such consignment shall be treated as unclaimed.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration may,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an unclaimed consignment which is perishable in nature, sell such consignment`
  line `in the manner provided in clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 83; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an unclaimed consignment which is not perishable in nature, cause a notice to`
  line `be served upon the consignee if his name and address are known, and upon the consignor if the name`
  line `and address of the consignee are not known, requiring him to remove the goods within a period of`
  line `seven days from the receipt thereof and if such notice cannot be served or there is a failure to comply`
  line `with the requisition in the notice, sell such consignment in the manner provided in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 83.`
  line
  line `(3) The railway administration shall, out of the sale proceeds received under sub-section (2), retain a`
  line `sum equal to the freight and other charges including expenses for the sale due to it and the surplus, if any,`
  line `of such sale proceeds shall be rendered to the person entitled thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (17971)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 112
  title `Disposal of perishable consignments in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17971&sectionno=85&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where by reason of any`
  line `flood, land-slip, breach of any lines of rails, collision between trains, derailment of, or other accident to a`
  line `train or any other cause, traffic on any route is interrupted and there is no likelihood of early resumption`
  line `of such traffic, nor is there any other reasonable route whereby traffic of perishable consignment may be`
  line `diverted to prevent, loss or deterioration of, or damage to, such consignment, the railway administration`
  line `may sell them in the manner provided in clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 83.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration shall, out of the sale proceeds received under sub-section (1), retain a`
  line `sum equal to the freight and other charges including expenses for the sale due to it and the surplus, if any,`
  line `of such sale proceeds, shall be rendered to the person entitled thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (17972)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 113
  title `Sales under sections 83 to 85 not to affect the right to suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17972&sectionno=86&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter, the right of sale under sections 83 to 85 shall be without prejudice to the right`
  line `of the railway administration to recover by suit, any freight, charge, amount or other expenses due to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (17973)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 114
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17973&sectionno=87&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) goods in respect of which no forwarding note shall be executed under proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(b) dangerous and offensive goods for the purposes of sub- section (1) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(c) infectious or contagious diseases for the purposes of section 68;`
  line
  line `(d) rates of penalty charges under section 73;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the consignment may be delivered without a railway receipt under`
  line `section 76;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of delivery of consignment or the sale proceeds to the person entitled thereto under`
  line `section 77;`
  line
  line `(g) the conditions subject to which and charges payable for allowing weighment and`
  line `circumstances for not allowing weighment of consignment in wagon-load or train-load under`
  line `section 79;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of giving open delivery under section 81;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of partial delivery certificate under sub-section (2) of section 82;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of sale of consignment or part thereof under the proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 83;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which a notice under sub-section (3) of section 83 may be given;`
  line `(l) generally, for regulating the carriage of goods by the railways.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this section may provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to one hundred and fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Every railway administration shall keep at each station a copy of the rules for the time being in`
  line `force under this section, and shall allow any person to refer to it free of charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (17974)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 115
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17974&sectionno=88&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "essential commodity" means an essential commodity as defined in clause (a) of section 2 of`
  line `the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(b) "notified station" means a station declared to be a notified station under section 89;`
  line
  line `(c) "State Government", in relation to a notified station, means the Government of the State in`
  line `which such station is situated, or where such station is situated in a Union territory, the administrator`
  line `of that Union territory appointed under article 239 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (17975)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 116
  title `Power to declare notified stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17975&sectionno=89&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, if it is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary that goods entrusted for carriage by train intended solely for the carriage of goods to any`
  line `railway station should be removed without delay from such railway station, declare, by notification, such`
  line `railway station to be a notified station for such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before declaring any railway station to be a notified station under this sub-section, the`
  line `Central Government shall have regard to all or any of the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the volume of traffic and the storage space available at such railway station;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature and quantities of goods generally booked to such railway station;`
  line
  line `(c) the scope for causing scarcity of such goods by not removing them for long periods from such`
  line `railway station and the hardship which such scarcity may cause to the community;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of wagons likely to be held up at such railway station if goods are not removed`
  line `therefrom quickly and the need for quick movement and availability of such wagons;`
  line
  line `(e) such other factors (being relevant from the point of view of the interest of the general public)`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the period specified in any notification issued under this sub-section in respect`
  line `of any railway station shall not exceed six months in the first instance, but such period may, by`
  line `notification, be extended from time to time by a period not exceeding six months on each occasion.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person entrusting any goods to a railway administration to be carried to a notified station`
  line `makes an application in such form and manner as may be prescribed and specifies therein the address of`
  line `the person to whom intimation by registered post of the arrival of the goods at the notified station shall be`
  line `given and pays the postage charges required for giving such intimation, the railway administration shall,`
  line `as soon as may be after the arrival of the goods at the notified station, send such intimation accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be exhibited at a conspicuous place at each notified station a statement in the`
  line `prescribed form setting out the description of the goods which by reason of the fact that they have not`
  line `been removed from the station within a period of seven days from the termination of transit thereof are`
  line `liable to be sold, in accordance with the provision, of sub-section (1) of section 90 by public auction and`
  line `the dates on which they would be so sold:`
  line
  line `Provided that different statements may be so exhibited in respect of goods proposed to be sold on`
  line `different dates.`
  line
  line `(4) If the goods specified in any statement to be exhibited under sub-section (3) include essential`
  line `commodities, the railway servant preparing the statement shall, as soon as may be after the preparation of`
  line `such statement, forward a copy thereof to--`
  line
  line `(a) the representative of the Central Government nominated by that Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) the representative of the State Government nominated by that Government in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(c) the District Magistrate within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the railway station is`
  line situated.
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (17976)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 117
  title `Disposal of unremoved goods at notified stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17976&sectionno=90&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any goods entrusted for carriage to`
  line `any notified station by a train intended solely for the carriage of goods are not removed from such station`
  line `by a person entitled to do so within a period of seven days after the termination of transit thereof at such`
  line `station, the railway administration may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), sell such goods by`
  line `public auction and apart from exhibiting, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of section`
  line `89, a statement containing a description of such goods, it shall not be necessary to give any notice of such`
  line `public auction, but the date on which such auction may be held under this sub-section may be notified in`
  line `one or more local newspapers, or where there are no such newspapers, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if at any time before the sale of such goods under this sub-section, the person entitled`
  line `thereto pays the freight and other charges and the expenses due in respect thereof to the railway`
  line `administration, he shall be allowed to remove such goods.`
  line
  line `(2) If any goods which may be sold by public auction under sub-section (1) at a notified station, being`
  line `essential commodities, are required by the Central Government or the State Government for its own use`
  line `or if the Central Government or such State Government considers that it is necessary for securing the`
  line `availability of all or any such essential commodities at fair prices so to do, it may, by order in writing,`
  line `direct the railway servant in-charge of such auction to transfer such goods to it or to such agency,`
  line `co-operative society or other person (being an agency, co-operative society or other person subject to the`
  line `control of the Government) engaged in the business of selling such essential commodities as may be`
  line `specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Every direction issued under sub-section (2) in respect of any essential commodity shall be`
  line `binding on the railway servant to whom it is issued and the railway administration and it shall be a`
  line `sufficient defence against any claim by the person entitled to the goods that such essential commodities`
  line `have been transferred in compliance with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) such direction shall not be binding on such railway servant or the railway administration`
  line
  line `(i) if it has not been received by the railway servant sufficiently in time to enable him to`
  line `prevent the sale of the essential commodities to which it relates; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if before the time appointed for such sale, the person entitled to such goods pays the`
  line `freight and other charges and the expenses due in respect thereof and claims that he be allowed to`
  line `remove the goods; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if the price payable for such goods (as estimated by the Central Government or, as the`
  line `case may be, the State Government) is not credited to the railway administration in the prescribed`
  line `manner and the railway administration is not indemnified against any additional amount which it`
  line `may become liable to pay towards the price by reason of the price not having been computed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4);`
  line
  line `(b) where directions are issued in respect of the same goods both by the Central Government and`
  line `the State Government, the directions received earlier shall prevail.`
  line
  line `(4) The price payable for any essential commodity transferred in compliance with a direction issued`
  line `under sub-section (2) shall be the price calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955).`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any essential commodity being a food-stuff in respect whereof a notification`
  line `issued under sub-section (3A) of section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955) is in`
  line `force in the locality in which the notified station is situated, the price payable shall be calculated in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clauses (iii) and (iv) of that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an essential commodity being any grade or variety of foodgrains, edible oilseeds`
  line `or edible oils in respect were of no notification issued under sub-section (3A) of section 3 of the`
  line `Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), is in force in the locality in which the notified station`
  line `is situated, the price payable shall be calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3B)`
  line `of that section;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an essential commodity being any kind of sugar in respect whereof no`
  line `notification issued under sub-section (3A) of section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955`
  line `(10 of 1955), is in force in the locality in which the notified station is situated, the price payable shall,`
  line `if such sugar has been booked by them producer to himself, be calculated in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (3C) of that section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the expressions "producer" and "sugar" shall have`
  line `the meanings a signed to these expressions in the Explanation to sub-section (3C) of section 3, and`
  line `clause (e) of section 2 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955), respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (17977)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 118
  title `Price to be paid to person entitled after deducting dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17977&sectionno=91&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) Out of the proceeds of any sale`
  line `of goods under sub-section (1) of section 90 or the price payable therefor under sub-section (4) of that`
  line `section, the railway administration may retain a sum equal to the freight and other charges due in respect`
  line `of such goods and the expenses incurred in respect of the goods and the auction thereof and render the`
  line `surplus, if any, to the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the railway administration may recover by`
  line `suit any such freight or charge or expenses referred to therein or balance thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Any goods sold under sub-section (1) of section 90 or transferred in compliance with the`
  line `directions issued under sub-section (2) of that section shall vest in the buyer or the transferee free from all`
  line `encumbrances but subject to a priority being given for the sum which may be retained by a railway`
  line `administration under sub-section (1), the person in whose favour such encumbrance subsits may have a`
  line `claim in respect of such encumbrance against the surplus, if any, referred to in that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (17978)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 119
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17978&sectionno=92&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the factors to which the Central Government shall have regard under clause (e) of the first`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which an application may be made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 89;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which a statement is required to be exhibited under sub-section (3) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the dates of public auctions may be notified under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 90;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of crediting to the railway administration the price of goods referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (iii) of clause (a) of the proviso to sub-section (3) of section 90.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (17979)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 120
  title `General responsibility of a railway administration as carrier of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17979&sectionno=93&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, a railway administration shall be responsible for the loss, destruction, damage or`
  line `deterioration in transit, or non-delivery of any consignment, arising from any cause except the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) act of God;`
  line
  line `(b) act of war;`
  line
  line `(c) act of public enemies;`
  line
  line `(d) arrest, restraint or seizure under legal process;`
  line
  line `(e) orders or restrictions imposed by the Central Government or a State Government or by an`
  line `officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government or a State Government authorised by it in`
  line `this behalf;`
  line
  line `(f) act or omission or negligence of the consignor or the consignee or the endorsee or the agent or`
  line `servant of the consignor or the consignee or the endorsee;`
  line
  line `(g) natural deterioration or wastage in bulk or weight due to inherent defect, quality or vice of the`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(h) latent defects;`
  line
  line `(i) fire, explosion or any unforeseen risk:`
  line
  line `Provided that even where such loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery is proved to`
  line `have arisen from any one or more of the aforesaid causes, the railway administration shall not be relieved`
  line `of its responsibility for the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery unless the railway`
  line `administration further proves that it has used reasonable foresight and care in the carriage of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (17980)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 121
  title `Goods to be loaded or delivered at a siding not belonging to a railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17980&sectionno=94&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where goods are required to be loaded at a siding not belonging to a railway administration for`
  line `carriage by railway, the railway administration shall not be responsible for any loss, destruction, damage`
  line `or deterioration of such goods from whatever cause arising, until the wagon containing the goods has`
  line `been placed at the specified point of interchange of wagons between the siding and the railway`
  line `administration and a railway servant authorised in this behalf has been informed in writing accordingly by`
  line `the owner of the siding.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any consignment is required to be delivered by a railway administration at a siding not`
  line `belonging to a railway administration, the railway administration shall not be responsible for any loss,`
  line `destruction, damage or deterioration or non-delivery of such consignment from whatever cause arising`
  line `after the wagon containing the consignment has been placed at the specified point of interchange of`
  line `wagons between the railway and the siding and the owner of the siding has been informed in writing`
  line `accordingly by a railway by a railway servant authorised in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (17981)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 122
  title `Delay or detention in transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17981&sectionno=95&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration shall not be responsible for the loss,`
  line `destruction, damage or deterioration of any consignment proved by the owner to have been caused by the`
  line `delay or detention in their carriage if the railway administration proves that the delay or detention arose`
  line `for reasons beyond its control or without negligence or misconduct on its part or on the part of any of its`
  line servants.
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (17982)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 123
  title `Traffic passing over railways in India and railways in foreign countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17982&sectionno=96&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `Where in the`
  line `course of carriage of any consignment from a place in India to a place outside India or from a place`
  line `outside India to a place in India or from one place outside India to another place outside India or from one`
  line `place in India to another place in India over any territory outside India, it is carried over the railways of`
  line `any railway administration in India, the railway administration shall not be responsible under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter for the loss, destruction, damage or deterioration of the goods, from whatever`
  line `cause arising, unless it is proved by the owner of the goods that such loss, destruction, damage or`
  line `deterioration arose over the railway of the railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (17983)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 124
  title `Goods carried at owner’s risk rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17983&sectionno=97&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 93, a`
  line `railway administration shall not be responsible for any loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or nondelivery`
  line `in transit, of any consignment carried at owners risk rate, from whatever cause arising, except`
  line `upon proof, that such loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery was due to negligence or`
  line `misconduct on its part or on the part of any of its servants:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the whole of such consignment or the whole of any package forming part of such`
  line `consignment is not delivered to the consignee or the endorsee and such non-delivery is not proved by`
  line `the railway administration to have been due to fire or to any accident to the train; or`
  line
  line `(b) where in respect of any such consignment or of any package forming part of such`
  line `consignment which had been so covered or protected that the covering or protection was not readily`
  line `removable by hand, it is pointed out to the railway administration on or before delivery that any part`
  line `of that consignment or package had been pilfered in transit,`
  line `the railway administration shall be bound to disclose to the consignor, the consignee or the endorsee how`
  line `the consignment or the package was dealt with throughout the time it was in its possession or control, but`
  line `if negligence or misconduct on the part of the railway administration or of any of its servants cannot be`
  line `fairly inferred from such disclosure, the burden of proving such negligence or misconduct shall lie on the`
  line `consignor, the consignee or the endorsee.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (17984)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 125
  title `Goods in defective condition or defectively packed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17984&sectionno=98&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, when any goods entrusted to a railway administration for`
  line carriage--
  line
  line `(a) are in a defective condition as a consequence of which they are liable to damage,`
  line `deterioration, leakage or wastage; or`
  line
  line `(b) are either defectively packed or not packed in such manner as may be prescribed and as a`
  line `result of such defective or improper packing are liable to damage, deterioration, leakage or wastage,`
  line `and the fact of such condition or defective or improper packing has been recorded by the consignor or his`
  line `agent in the forwarding note, the railway administration shall not be responsible for any damage,`
  line `deterioration, leakage or wastage or for the condition in which such goods are available for delivery at`
  line `destination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the railway administration shall be responsible for any such damage, deterioration,`
  line `leakage or wastage or for the condition in which such goods are available for delivery at destination if`
  line `negligence or misconduct on the part of the railway administration or of any of its servants is proved.`
  line
  line `(2) When any goods entrusted to a railway administration for carriage are found on arrival at the`
  line `destination station to have been damaged or to have suffered deterioration, leakage or wastage, the`
  line `railway administration shall not be responsible for the damage, deterioration, leakage or wastage of the`
  line `goods on proof by railway administration,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the goods were, at the time of entrustment to the railway administration, in a defective`
  line `condition, or were at that time either defectively packed or not packed in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and as a result of which were liable to damage, deterioration, leakage or wastage; and`
  line
  line `(b) that such defective condition or defective or improper packing was not brought to the notice`
  line `of the railway administration or any of its servants at the time of entrustment of the goods to the`
  line `railway administration for carriage by railway:`
  line
  line `Provided that the railway administration shall be responsible for any such damage, deterioration,`
  line `leakage or wastage if negligence or misconduct on the part of the railway administration or of any of its`
  line `servants is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (17985)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 126
  title `Responsibility of a railway administration after termination of transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17985&sectionno=99&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway`
  line `administration shall be responsible as a bailee under sections 151, 152 and 161 of the Indian Contract Act,`
  line `1872 (9 of 1872), for the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of any consignment up`
  line `to a period of seven days after the termination of transit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the consignment is at owners risk rate, the railway administration shall not be`
  line `responsible as a bailee for such loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery except on proof of`
  line `negligence or misconduct on the part of the railway administration or of any of its servants.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration shall not be responsible in any case for the loss, destruction, damage,`
  line `deterioration or non-delivery of any consignment arising after the expiry of a period of seven days after`
  line `the termination of transit.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, a railway`
  line `administration shall not be responsible for the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of perishable goods, animals, explosives and such dangerous or other goods as may be prescribed, after the`
  line `termination of transit.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this section shall affect the liability of any person to pay`
  line `any demurrage or wharfage, as the case may be, for so long as the consignment is not unloaded from the`
  line `railway wagons or removed from the railway premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (17986)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 127
  title `Responsibility as carrier of luggage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17986&sectionno=100&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration shall not be responsible for the`
  line `loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of any luggage unless a railway servant has`
  line `booked the luggage and given a receipt therefor and in the case of luggage which is carried by the`
  line `passenger in his charge, unless it is also proved that the loss, destruction, damage or deterioration was due`
  line `to the negligence or misconduct on its part or on the part of any of its servants.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (17987)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 128
  title `Responsibility as a carrier of animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17987&sectionno=101&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `A railway administration shall not be responsible for`
  line `any loss or destruction of, or injuries to, any animal carried by railway arising from freight or restiveness`
  line `of the animal or from overloading of wagons by the consignor.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (17988)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 129
  title `Exoneration from liability in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17988&sectionno=102&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter, a railway administration shall not be responsible for the loss,`
  line `destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of any consignment,--`
  line
  line `(a) when such loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery is due to the fact that a`
  line `materially false description of the consignment is given in the statement delivered under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 66; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a fraud has been practised by the consignor or the consignee or the endorsee or by an`
  line `agent of the consignor, consignee or the endorsee; or`
  line
  line `(c) where it is proved by the railway administration to have been caused by, or to have arisen`
  line from--
  line
  line `(i) improper loading or unloading by the consignor or the consignee or the endorsee or by an`
  line `agent of the consignor, consignee or the endorsee;`
  line
  line `(ii) riot, civil commotion, strike, lock-out, stoppage or restraint of labour from whatever`
  line `cause arising whether partial or general; or`
  line
  line `(d) for any indirect or consequential loss or damage or for loss of particular market.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (17989)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 130
  title `Extent of monetary liability in respect of any consignment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17989&sectionno=103&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any consignment is`
  line `entrusted to a railway administration for carriage by railway and the value of such consignment has not`
  line `been declared as required under sub-section (2) by the consignor, the amount of liability of the railway`
  line `administration for the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of the consignment shall in`
  line `no case exceed such amount calculated with reference to the weight of the consignment as may be`
  line `prescribed, and where such consignment consists of an animal, the liability shall not exceed such amount`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the consignor declares the value of`
  line `any consignment at the time of its entrustment to a railway administration for carriage by railway, and`
  line `pays such percentage charge as may be prescribed on so much of the value of such consignment as is in`
  line `excess of the liability of the railway administration as calculated or specified, as the case may be, under`
  line `sub-section (1), the liability of the railway administration for the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration`
  line `or non-delivery of such consignment shall not exceed the value so declared.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, from time to time, by notification, direct that such goods as may be`
  line `specified in the notification shall not be accepted for carriage by railway unless the value of such goods is`
  line `declared and percentage charge is paid as required under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (17990)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 131
  title `Extent of liability in respect of goods carried in open wagon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17990&sectionno=104&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Where any goods, which,`
  line `under ordinary circumstances, would be carried in covered wagon and would be liable to damage, if`
  line `carried otherwise, are with the consent of the consignor, recorded in the forwarding note, carried in open`
  line `wagon, the responsibility of railway administration for destruction, damage or deterioration which may arise only by reason of the goods being so carried, shall be one-half of the amount of liability for such`
  line `destruction, damage or deterioration determined under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (17991)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 132
  title `Right of railway administration to check contents of certain consignment or luggage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17991&sectionno=105&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Where the value has been declared under section 103 in respect of any consignment a railway`
  line `administration may make it a condition of carrying such consignment that a railway servant authorised by`
  line `it in this behalf has been satisfied by examination or otherwise that the consignment tendered for carriage`
  line `contain the articles declared.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (17992)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 133
  title `Notice of claim for compensation and refund of overcharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17992&sectionno=106&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be`
  line `entitled to claim compensation against a railway administration for the loss, destruction, damage,`
  line `deterioration or non-delivery of goods carried by railway, unless a notice thereof is served by him or on`
  line `his behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) to the railway administration to which the goods are entrusted for carriage; or`
  line
  line `(b) to the railway administration on whose railway the destination station lies, or the loss,`
  line `destruction, damage or deterioration occurs,`
  line
  line `within a period of six months from the date of entrustment of the goods.`
  line
  line `(2) Any information demanded or enquiry made in writing from, or any complaint made in writing to,`
  line `any of the railway administrations mentioned in sub-section (1) by or on behalf of the person within the`
  line `said period of six months regarding the non-delivery or delayed delivery of the goods with particulars`
  line `sufficient to identify the goods shall, for the purpose of this section, be deemed to be a notice of claim for`
  line compensation.
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be entitled to a refund of an overcharge in respect of goods carried by railway`
  line `unless a notice therefor has been served by him or on his behalf to the railway administration to which the`
  line `overcharge has been paid within six months from the date of such payment or the date of delivery of such`
  line `goods at the destination station, whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (17993)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 134
  title `Applications for compensation for loss, etc., of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17993&sectionno=107&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `An application for compensation for`
  line `loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of goods shall be filed against the railway`
  line `administration on whom a notice under section 106 has been served.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (17994)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 135
  title `Person entitled to claim compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17994&sectionno=108&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a railway administration pays compensation for`
  line `the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of goods entrusted to it for carriage, to the`
  line `consignee or the endorsee producing the railway receipt, the railway administration shall be deemed to`
  line `have discharged its liability and no application before the Claims Tribunal or any other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the railway administration on the ground that the consignee or the endorsee was not`
  line `legally entitled to receive such compensation.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any person having any interest in the goods to`
  line `enforce the same against the consignee or the endorsee receiving compensation under that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (17995)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 136
  title `Railway administration against which application for compensation for personal injury is to be filed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17995&sectionno=109&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `An application before the Claims Tribunal for compensation for the loss of life or personal`
  line `injury to a passenger, may be instituted against,--`
  line
  line `(a) the railway administration from which the passenger obtained his pass or purchased his ticket,`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) the railway administration on whose railway the destination station lies or the loss or personal`
  line `injury occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (17996)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 137
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17996&sectionno=110&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `In an application before the Claims Tribunal for compensation for loss,`
  line `destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of any goods, the burden of proving--`
  line
  line `(a) the monetary loss actually sustained; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the value has been declared under sub-section (2) of section 103 in respect of any`
  line `consignment that the value so declared is its true value, shall lie on the person claiming compensation, but subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, it`
  line
  line `shall not be necessary for him to prove how the loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery`
  line `was caused.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (17997)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 138
  title `Extent of liability of railway administration in respect of accidents at sea.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17997&sectionno=111&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `railway administration contracts to carry passengers or goods partly by railway and partly by sea, a`
  line `condition exempting the railway administration from responsibility for any loss of life, personal injury or`
  line `loss of or damage to goods which may happen during the carriage by sea from act of God, public`
  line `enemies, fire, accidents from machinery, boilers and steam and all and every other dangers and accidents`
  line `of the seas, rivers and navigation of whatever nature and kind shall, without being expressed, be deemed`
  line `to be part of the contract, and, subject to that condition, the railway administration shall, irrespective of`
  line `the nationality or ownership of the ship used for the carriage by sea, be responsible for any loss of life,`
  line `personal injury or loss of or damage to goods which may happen during the carriage by sea, to the extent`
  line `to which it would be responsible under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), if the ships were`
  line `registered under that Act and the railway administration were owner of the ship and not to any greater`
  line extent.
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving that any such loss, injury or damage as is mentioned in sub-section (1)`
  line `happened during the carriage by sea shall lie on the railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (17998)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 139
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17998&sectionno=112&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of packing of goods entrusted to a railway administration under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 98;`
  line
  line `(b) the goods for the purposes of sub-section (3) of section 99; and`
  line
  line `(c) the maximum amount payable by the railway administration for the loss, destruction, damage,`
  line `deterioration or non-delivery of any consignment under sub-section (1) of section 103.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (17999)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 140
  title `Notice of railway accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=17999&sectionno=113&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the course of working a railway,`
  line
  line `(a) any accident attended with loss of any human life, or with grievous hurt, as defined in the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), or with such serious injury to property as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) any collision between trains of which one is a train carrying passengers; or`
  line
  line `(c) the derailment of any train carrying passengers, or of any part of such train; or`
  line
  line `(d) any accident of a description usually attended with loss of human life or with such grievous`
  line `hurt as aforesaid or with serious injury to property; or`
  line
  line `(e) any accident of any other description which the Central Government may notify in this behalf`
  line `in the Official Gazette,br`
  line
  line `occurs, the station master of the station nearest to the place at which the accident occurs or where there is`
  line `no station master, the railway servant in charge of the section of the railway on which the accident occurs,`
  line `shall, without delay, give notice of the accident to the District Magistrate and Superintendent of Police,`
  line `within whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, the officer in charge of the police station within the local`
  line `limits of which the accident occurs and to such other Magistrate or police officer as may be appointed in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The railway administration within whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, as also the railway`
  line `administration to whom the train involved in the accident belongs, shall without delay, give notice of the`
  line `accident to the State Government and the Commissioner having jurisdiction over the place of the`
  line accident.
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (18000)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 141
  title `Inquiry by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18000&sectionno=114&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the receipt of a notice under section 113 of the occurrence`
  line `of an accident to a train carrying passengers resulting in loss of human life or grievous hurt causing total`
  line `or partial disablement of permanent nature to a passenger or serious damage to railway property, the`
  line `Commissioner shall, as soon as may be, notify the railway administration in whose jurisdiction the`
  line `accident occurred of his intention to hold an inquiry into the causes that led to the accident and shall at the`
  line `same time fix and communicate the date, time and place of inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be open to the Commissioner to hold an inquiry into any other accident which,`
  line `in his opinion, requires the holding of such an inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) If for any reason, the Commissioner is not able to hold an inquiry as soon as may be after the`
  line `occurrence of the accident, he shall notify the railway administration accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (18001)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 142
  title `Inquiry by railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18001&sectionno=115&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Where no inquiry is held by the Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 114 or where the Commissioner has informed the railway administration under`
  line `sub-section (2) of that section that he is not able to hold an inquiry, the railway administration within`
  line `whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, shall cause an inquiry to be made in accordance with the`
  line `prescribed procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (18002)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 143
  title `Powers of Commissioner in relation to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18002&sectionno=116&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of conducting an`
  line `inquiry under this Chapter into the causes of any accident on a railway, the Commissioner shall, in`
  line `addition to the powers specified in section 7, have the powers as are vested in a civil court while trying a`
  line `suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner while conducting an inquiry under this Chapter shall be deemed to be a Civil`
  line `Court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (18003)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 144
  title `Statement made before Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18003&sectionno=117&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `No statement made by a person in the course of`
  line `giving evidence in an inquiry before the Commissioner shall subject him to, or be used against him in,`
  line `any civil or criminal proceeding, except a prosecution for giving false evidence by such statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement is--`
  line
  line `(a) made in reply to a question which is required by the Commissioner to answer; or`
  line
  line `(b) relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (18004)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 145
  title `Procedure, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18004&sectionno=118&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `Any railway administration or the Commissioner conducting an inquiry under`
  line `this Chapter may send notice of the inquiry to such persons, follow such procedure, and prepare the report`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (18005)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 146
  title `No inquiry, investigation, etc., to be made if the Commission of Inquiry is appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18005&sectionno=119&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, where a Commission of`
  line `Inquiry is appointed under the Commissions of Inquiry Act, 1952 (3 of 1952), to inquire into an accident,`
  line `any inquiry, investigation or other proceeding pending in relation to that accident shall not be proceeded`
  line `with, and all records or other documents relating to such inquiry shall be forwarded to such authority as`
  line `may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (18006)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 147
  title `Inquiry into accident not covered by section 113.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18006&sectionno=120&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Where any accident of the nature not`
  line `specified in section 113 occurs in the course of working a railway, the railway administration within`
  line `whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, may cause such inquiry to be made into the causes of the accident,`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (18007)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 148
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18007&sectionno=121&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `Every railway administration shall send to the Central Government, a return of`
  line `accidents occurring on its railway, whether attended with injury to any person or not, in such form and`
  line `manner and at such intervals as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (18008)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 149
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18008&sectionno=122&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the injury to property which shall be considered serious under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 113;`
  line
  line `(b) the forms of notice of accidents to be given under section 113 and the particulars of the`
  line `accident such notices shall contain;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of sending the notices of accidents, including the class of accidents to be sent`
  line `immediately after the accident;`
  line
  line `(d) the duties of the Commissioner, railway administration, railway servants, police officers and`
  line `Magistrates on the occurrence of an accident;`
  line
  line `(e) the persons to whom notices in respect of any inquiry under this Chapter are to be sent, the`
  line `procedure to be followed in such inquiry and the manner in which a report of such inquiry shall be`
  line prepared;
  line
  line `(f) the nature of inquiry to be made by a railway administration into the causes of an accident`
  line `under section 120;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner of sending a return of accidents by a railway administration under`
  line `section 121.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (18009)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 150
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18009&sectionno=123&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "accident" means an accident of the nature described in section 124;`
  line
  line `(b) "dependant" means any of the following relatives of a deceased passenger, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the wife, husband, son and daughter, and in case the deceased passenger is unmarried or is`
  line `a minor, his parent;`
  line
  line `(ii) the parent, minor brother or unmarried sister, widowed sister, widowed daughter-in-law`
  line `and a minor child of a pre-deceased son, if dependant wholly or partly on the deceased passenger;`
  line
  line `(iii) a minor child of a pre-deceased daughter, if wholly dependant on the deceased passenger;`
  line
  line `(iv) the paternal grand parent wholly dependant on the deceased passenger;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) "untoward incident" means--`
  line
  line `(1) (i) the commission of a terrorist act within the meaning of sub-section (1) of section (3) of`
  line `the Terrorist and Disruptive Activities (Prevention) Act, 1987 (28 of 1987); or`
  line
  line `(ii) the making of a violent attack or the commission of robbery or dacoity; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the indulging in rioting, shoot-out or arson, by any person in or on any train carrying passengers, or in a waiting hall, cloak room or`
  line `reservation or booking office or on any platform or in any other place within the precincts of a`
  line `railway station; or`
  line
  line `(2) the accidental falling of any passenger from a train carrying passengers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (18010)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 151
  title `Extent of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18010&sectionno=124&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `When in the course of working a railway, an accident occurs, being either a`
  line `collision between trains of which one is a train carrying passengers or the derailment of or other accident`
  line `to a train or any part of a train carrying passengers, then whether or not there has been any wrongful act,`
  line `neglect or default on the part of the railway administration such as would entitle a passenger who has`
  line `been injured or has suffered a loss to maintain an action and recover damages in respect thereof, the`
  line `railway administration shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, be liable to pay`
  line `compensation to such extent as may be prescribed and to that extent only for loss occasioned by the death`
  line `of a passenger dying as a result of such accident, and for personal injury and loss, destruction, damage or`
  line `deterioration of goods owned by the passenger and accompanying him in his compartment or on the train,`
  line `sustained as a result of such accident.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section "passenger" includes a railway servant on duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124_a:
  sectionId (18011)
  sectionNo 124A
  orderNo 152
  title `Compensation on account of untoward incidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18011&sectionno=124A&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_124_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[124A. Compensation on account of untoward incidents.-- When in the course of working a`
  line `railway an untoward incident occurs, then whether or not there has been any wrongful act, neglect or`
  line `default on the part of the railway administration such as would entitle a passenger who has been injured or`
  line `the dependant of a passenger who has been killed to maintain an action and recover damages in respect`
  line `thereof, the railway administration shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, be liable to`
  line `pay compensation to such extent as may be prescribed and to that extent only of loss occasioned by the`
  line `death of, or injury to, a passenger as a result of such untoward incident:`
  line
  line `Provided that no compensation shall be payable under this section by the railway administration if the`
  line `passenger dies or suffers injury due to--`
  line
  line `(a) suicide or attempted suicide by him;`
  line
  line `(b) self-inflicted injury;`
  line
  line `(c) his own criminal act;`
  line
  line `(d) any act committed by him in a state of intoxication or insanity;`
  line
  line `(e) any natural cause or disease or medical or surgical treatment unless such treatment becomes`
  line `necessary due to injury caused by the said untoward incident.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, "passenger" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a railway servant on duty; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a person who has purchased a valid ticket for travelling, by a train carrying passengers, on any`
  line `date or a valid platform ticket and becomes a victim of an untoward incident.]`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (18012)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 153
  title `Application for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18012&sectionno=125&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for compensation under section 124 ^1[or`
  line `section 124A] may be made to the Claims Tribunal--`
  line
  line `(a) by the person who has sustained the injury or suffered any loss, or`
  line
  line `(b) by any agent duly authorised by such person in this behalf, or`
  line
  line `(c) where such person is a minor, by his guardian, or`
  line
  line `(d) where death has resulted from the accident ^2[or the untoward incident], by any dependant of`
  line `the deceased or where such a dependant is a minor, by his guardian.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application by a dependant for compensation under this section shall be for the benefit of`
  line `every other dependant.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (18013)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 154
  title `Interim relief by railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18013&sectionno=126&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person who has made an application`
  line `for compensation under section 125 desires to be paid interim relief, he may apply to the railway`
  line `administration for payment of interim relief along with a copy of the application made under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, on the receipt of an application made under sub-section (1) and after making such inquiry`
  line `as it may deem fit, the railway administration is satisfied that circumstances exist which require relief to`
  line `be afforded to the applicant immediately, it may, pending determination by the Claims Tribunal of the`
  line `actual amount of compensation payable under section 124 ^1[or section 124A] pay to any person who has`
  line `sustained the injury or suffered any loss, or where death has resulted from the accident, to any dependant`
  line `of the deceased, such sum as it considers reasonable for affording such relief, so however, that the sum`
  line `paid shall not exceed the amount of compensation payable at such rates as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The railway administration shall, as soon as may be, after making an order regarding payment of`
  line `interim relief under sub-section (2), send a copy thereof to the Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Any sum paid by the railway administration under sub-section (2) shall be taken into account by`
  line `the Claims Tribunal while determining the amount of compensation payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (18014)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 155
  title `Determination of compensation in respect of any injury or loss of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18014&sectionno=127&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to`
  line `such rules as may be made, the rates of compensation payable in respect of any injury shall be determined`
  line `by the Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation payable in respect of any loss of goods shall be such as the Claims Tribunal`
  line `may, having regard to the circumstances of the case, determine to be reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (18015)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 156
  title `Saving as to certain rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18015&sectionno=128&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right of any person to claim compensation under`
  line `section 124 ^1[or section 124A] shall not affect the right of any such person to recover compensation`
  line `payable under the Workmens Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923), or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force; but no person shall be entitled to claim compensation more than once in respect of the same`
  line accident.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any person to claim compensation payable`
  line `under any contract or scheme providing for payment of compensation for death or personal injury or for`
  line `damage to property or any sum payable under any policy of insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (18016)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 157
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18016&sectionno=129&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the compensation payable for death;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature of the injuries for which compensation shall be paid and the amount of such`
  line compensation.
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (18017)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 158
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18017&sectionno=130&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) the employment of a railway servant is said to be "continuous" except when it is excluded or`
  line `has been declared to be essentially intermittent or intensive;`
  line
  line `(b) the employment of a railway servant is said to be "essentially intermittent" when it has been`
  line `declared to be so by the prescribed authority on the ground that the daily hours of duty of the railway`
  line `servant normally include periods of inaction aggregating to fifty per cent. or more (including at least`
  line `one such period of not less than one hour or two such periods of not less than half an hour each) in a`
  line `tour of twelve hours duty (on the average over seventy-two consecutive hours), during which the railway servant may be on duty, but is not called upon to display either physical activity or sustained`
  line attention;
  line
  line `(c) the employment of a railway servant is said to be excluded, if he belongs to any one of the`
  line `following categories, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) railway servants employed in a managerial or confidential capacity;`
  line
  line `(ii) armed guards or other personnel subject to discipline similar to that of any of the armed`
  line `police forces;`
  line
  line `(iii) staff of the railway schools imparting technical training or academic education;`
  line
  line `(iv) such staff as may be specified as supervisory under the rules;`
  line
  line `(v) such other categories of staff as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) the employment of a railway servant is said to be "intensive" when it has been declared to be`
  line `so by the prescribed authority on the ground that it is of a strenuous nature involving continued`
  line `concentration or hard manual labour with little or no period of relaxation.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (18018)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 159
  title `Chapter not to apply to certain railway servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18018&sectionno=131&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall apply to any`
  line `railway servant to whom the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948) or the Mines Act 1952 (35 of 1952) or the`
  line `Railway Protection Force Act, 1957 (23 of 1957) or the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958),`
  line applies.
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (18019)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 160
  title `Limitation of hours of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18019&sectionno=132&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway servant whose employment is essentially`
  line `intermittent shall not be employed for more than seventy-five hours in any week.`
  line
  line `(2) A railway servant whose employment is continuous shall not be employed for more than fifty-four`
  line `hours a week on an average in a two-weekly period of fourteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) A railway servant whose employment is intensive shall not be employed for more than forty-five`
  line `hours a week on an average in a two-weekly period of fourteen days.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such rules as may be prescribed, temporary exemptions of railway servants from the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) may be made by the prescribed`
  line `authority if it is of opinion that such temporary exemptions are necessary to avoid serious interference`
  line `with the ordinary working of the railway or in cases of accident, actual or threatened, or when urgent`
  line `work is required to be done to the railway or to rolling stock or in any emergency which could not have`
  line `been foreseen or prevented, or in other cases of exceptional pressure of work:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such exemption results in the increase of hours of employment of a railway`
  line `servant referred to in any of the sub-sections, he shall be paid overtime at not less than two times his`
  line `ordinary rate of pay for the excess hours of work.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (18020)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 161
  title `Grant of periodical rest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18020&sectionno=133&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, a railway servant`
  line
  line `(a) whose employment is intensive or continuous shall, for every week commencing on a Sunday,`
  line `be granted a rest of not less than thirty consecutive hours;`
  line
  line `(b) whose employment is essentially intermittent shall, for every week commencing on a Sunday,`
  line `be granted a rest of not less than twenty-four consecutive hours including a full night.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(i) any locomotive or traffic running staff shall be granted, each month, a rest of at least four`
  line `periods of not less than thirty consecutive hours each or at least five periods of not less than`
  line `twenty-two consecutive hours each, including a full night;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Central Government may, by rules, specify the railway servants to whom periods of rest`
  line `on scales less than those laid down under sub-section (1) may be granted and the periods thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, if the prescribed authority is of the opinion`
  line `that such circumstances as are referred to in sub-section (4) of section 132 are present, it may exempt any`
  line `railway servant from the provisions of sub-section (1) or clause (i) of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that a railway servant so exempted shall, in such circumstances as may be prescribed, be`
  line `granted compensatory periods of rest for the periods he has foregone.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (18021)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 162
  title `Railway servant to remain on duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18021&sectionno=134&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter or the rules made thereunder`
  line `shall, where due provision has been made for the relief of a railway servant, authorise him to leave his`
  line `duty until he has been relieved.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (18022)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 163
  title `Supervisors of railway labour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18022&sectionno=135&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, the`
  line `Central Government may appoint supervisors of railway labour.`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of supervisors of railways labour shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) to inspect railways in order to determine whether the provisions of this Chapter or of the rules`
  line `made thereunder are duly observed; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A supervisor of railway labour shall be deemed to be a Commissioner for the purposes of sections`
  line `7 and 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (18023)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 164
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18023&sectionno=136&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the authorities who may declare the employment of any railway servant essentially`
  line `intermittent or intensive;`
  line
  line `(b) the appeals against any such declaration and the manner in which, and the conditions subject`
  line `to which any such appeal may be filed and heard;`
  line
  line `(c) the categories of staff that may be specified under sub-clauses (iv) and (v) of clause (c) of`
  line `section 130;`
  line
  line `(d) the authorities by whom exemptions under sub-section (4) of section 132 or sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 133 may be made;`
  line
  line `(e) the delegation of power by the authorities referred to in clause (d);`
  line
  line `(f) the railway servant to whom clause (ii) of sub-section (2) of section 133 apply and the periods`
  line `of rest to be granted to them;`
  line
  line `(g) the appointment of supervisors of railway labour and their functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (18024)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 165
  title `Fraudulently travelling or attempting to travel without proper pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 56 of 2003, s. 2, for "fifty rupees" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18024&sectionno=137&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any`
  line `person, with intent to defraud a railway administration,--`
  line
  line `(a) enters or remains in any carriage on a railway or travels in a train in contravention of section`
  line `55, or`
  line
  line `(b) uses or attempts to use a single pass or a single ticket which has already been used on a`
  line `previous journey, or in the case of a return ticket, a half thereof which has already been so used,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such punishment shall not be less than a fine of five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The person referred to in sub-section (1) shall also be liable to pay the excess charge mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (3) in addition to the ordinary single fare for the distance which he has travelled, or where`
  line `there is any doubt as to the station from which he started, the ordinary single fare from the station from`
  line `which the train originally started, or if the tickets of passengers travelling in the train have been examined`
  line `since the original starting of the train, the ordinary single fare from the place where the tickets were so`
  line `examined or, in case of their having been examined more than once, were last examined.`
  line
  line `(3) The excess charge referred to in sub-section (2) shall be a sum equal to the ordinary single fare`
  line `referred to in that sub-section or ^1[two hundred and fifty rupees], whichever is more.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 65 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1960), the court`
  line `convicting an offender may direct that the person in default of payment of any fine inflicted by the court`
  line `shall suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (18025)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 166
  title `Levy of excess charge and fare for travelling without proper pass or ticket or beyond authorised distance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 56 of 2003, s. 2, for "fifty rupees" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18025&sectionno=138&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any passenger,--`
  line
  line `(a) being in or having alighted from a train, fails or refuses to present for examination or to`
  line `deliver up his pass or ticket immediately on a demand being made therefor under section 54, or`
  line
  line `(b) travels in a train in contravention of the provisions of section 55,`
  line `he shall be liable to pay, on the demand of any railway servant authorised in this behalf, the excess charge`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (3) in addition to the ordinary single fare for the distance which he has travelled`
  line `or, where there is any doubt as to the station from which he started, the ordinary single fare from the`
  line `station from which the train originally started, or, if the tickets of passengers travelling in the train have`
  line `been examined since the original starting of the train, the ordinary single fare from the place where the`
  line `tickets were so examined or in the case of their having been examined more than once, were last`
  line examined.
  line
  line `(2) If any passenger,--`
  line
  line `(a) travels or attempts to travel in or on a carriage, or by a train, of a higher class than that for`
  line `which he has obtained a pass or purchased a ticket; or`
  line
  line `(b) travels in or on a carriage beyond the place authorised by his pass or ticket,`
  line `he shall be liable to pay, on the demand of any railway servant authorised in this behalf, any difference`
  line `between the fare paid by him and the fare payable in respect of the journey he has made and the excess`
  line `charge referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) The excess charge shall be a sum equal to the amount payable under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), as the case may be, or ^1[two hundred and fifty rupees], whichever is more:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the passenger has with him a certificate granted under sub-section (2) of section 55,`
  line `no excess charge shall be payable.`
  line
  line `(4) If any passenger liable to pay the excess charge and the fare mentioned in sub-section (1), or the`
  line `excess charge and any difference of fare mentioned in sub-section (2), fails or refuses to pay the same on`
  line `a demand being made therefor under one or other of these sub-sections, as the case may be, any railway`
  line `servant authorised by the railway administration in this behalf may apply to any Metropolitan Magistrate`
  line `or a Judicial Magistrate of the first or second class, as the case may be, for the recovery of the sum`
  line `payable as if it were a fine, and the Magistrate if satisfied that the sum is payable shall order it to be so`
  line `recovered, and may order that the person liable for the payment shall in default of payment suffer`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one month but not less than ten days.`
  line
  line `(5) Any sum recovered under sub-section (4) shall, as and when it is recovered, be paid to the railway`
  line administration.
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (18026)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 167
  title `Power to remove persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18026&sectionno=139&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `Any person failing or refusing to pay the fare and the excess`
  line `charge referred to in section 138 may be removed by any railway servant authorised in this behalf who`
  line `may call to his aid any other person to effect such removal:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to preclude a person removed from a carriage of`
  line `a higher class from continuing his journey in a carriage of a class for which he holds a pass or ticket:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a woman or a child if unaccompanied by a male passenger, shall not be so`
  line `removed except either at the station from where she or he commences her or his journey or at a junction`
  line `or terminal station or station at the headquarters of a civil district and such removal shall be made only`
  line `during the day.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (18027)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 168
  title `Security for good behaviour in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18027&sectionno=140&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a court convicting a person of an`
  line `offence under section 137 or section 138 finds that he has been habitually committing or attempting to`
  line `commit that offence and the court is of the opinion that it is necessary or desirable to require that person`
  line `to execute a bond for good behaviour, such court may, at the time of passing the sentence on the person,`
  line `order him to execute a bond with or without sureties, for such amount and for such period not exceeding`
  line `three years as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) may also be made by an appellate court or by the High Court when`
  line `exercising its powers of revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (18028)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 169
  title `Needlessly interfering with means of communication in a train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18028&sectionno=141&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `If any passenger or any`
  line `other person, without reasonable and sufficient cause, makes use of, or interferes with, any means`
  line `provided by a railway administration in a train for communication between passengers and the railway`
  line `servant in charge of the train, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, where a passenger, without reasonable and sufficient cause, makes use of the alarm`
  line `chain provided by a railway administration, such punishment shall not be less than--`
  line
  line `(a) a fine of five hundred rupees, in the case of conviction for the first offence; and`
  line
  line `(b) imprisonment for three months in case of conviction for the second or subsequent offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (18029)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 170
  title `Penalty for transfer of tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18029&sectionno=142&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person not being a railway servant or an agent`
  line `authorised in this behalf`
  line
  line `(a) sells or attempts to sell any ticket or any half of a return ticket; or`
  line
  line `(b) parts or attempts to part with the possession of a ticket against which reservation of a seat or`
  line `berth has been made or any half of a return ticket or a season ticket,`
  line `in order to enable any other person to travel therewith, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with`
  line `both, and shall also forfeit the ticket which he sells or attempts to sell or parts or attempts to part.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person purchases any ticket referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) or obtains the`
  line `possession of any ticket referred to in clause (b) of that sub-section from any person other than a railway`
  line `servant or an agent authorised in this behalf, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three months and with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and if the purchaser`
  line `or holder of any ticket aforesaid travels or attempts to travel therewith, he shall forfeit the ticket which he`
  line `so purchased or obtained and shall be deemed to be travelling without a proper ticket and shall be liable to`
  line `be dealt with under section 138:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, the punishment under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not be less than a fine`
  line `of two hundred and fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (18030)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 171
  title `Penalty for unauthorised carrying on of business of procuring and supplying of railway tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18030&sectionno=143&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, not being a railway servant or an agent authorised in this behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) carries on the business of procuring and supplying tickets for travel on a railway or for`
  line `reserved accommodation for journey in a train; or`
  line
  line `(b) purchases or sells or attempts to purchase or sell tickets with a view to carrying on any such`
  line `business either by himself or by any other person,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both, and shall also forfeit the tickets which he so procures,`
  line `supplies, purchases, sells or attempts to purchase or sell:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such punishment shall not be less than imprisonment for a term of one month or a`
  line `fine of five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever abets any offence punishable under this section shall, whether or not such offence is`
  line `committed, be punishable with the same punishment as is provided for the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (18031)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 172
  title `Prohibition on hawking, etc., and begging.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-3-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18031&sectionno=144&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person canvasses for any custom or`
  line `hawks or exposes for sale any article whatsoever in any railway carriage or upon any part of a railway,`
  line `except under and in accordance with the terms and conditions of a licence granted by the railway`
  line `administration in this behalf, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such punishment shall not be less than a fine of one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) No person shall be permitted to beg in any railway carriage or upon any part of the railway.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any person referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may be removed from the railway carriage or any part of the railway or railway station, as the case may be, by any railway servant authorised in this behalf or by any other person whom such railway servant may call to his aid.`
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (18032)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 173
  title `Drunkenness or nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18032&sectionno=145&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `If any person in any railway carriage or upon any part of a`
  line railway--
  line
  line `(a) is in a state of intoxication; or`
  line
  line `(b) commits any nuisance or act of indecency or uses abusive or obscene language; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully or without excuse interferes with any amenity provided by the railway administration`
  line `so as to affect the comfortable travel of any passenger,`
  line
  line `he may be removed from the railway by any railway servant and shall, in addition to the forfeiture of his`
  line `pass or ticket, be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months and with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such punishment shall not be less than--`
  line
  line `(a) a fine of one hundred rupees in the case of conviction for the first offence; and`
  line
  line `(b) imprisonment of one month and a fine of two hundred and fifty rupees, in the case of`
  line `conviction for second or subsequent offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (18033)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 174
  title `Obstructing railway servant in his duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18033&sectionno=146&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully obstructs or prevents any`
  line `railway servant in the discharge of his duties, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (18034)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 175
  title `Trespass and refusal to desist from trespass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18034&sectionno=147&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person enters upon or into any part`
  line `of a railway without lawful authority, or having lawfully entered upon or into such part misuses such`
  line `property or refuses to leave, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such punishment shall not be less than a fine of five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person referred to in sub-section (1) may be removed from the railway by any railway servant`
  line `or by any other person whom such railway servant may call to his aid.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (18035)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 176
  title `Penalty for making a false statement in an application for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18035&sectionno=148&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `If in any`
  line `application for compensation under section 125, any person makes a statement which is false or which he`
  line `knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (18036)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 177
  title `Making a false claim for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18036&sectionno=149&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `If any person requiring compensation from a railway`
  line `administration for loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of any consignment makes a`
  line `claim which is false or which he knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (18037)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 178
  title `Maliciously wrecking or attempting to wreck a train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18037&sectionno=150&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), if any person unlawfully,--`
  line
  line `(a) puts or throws upon or across any railway, any wood, stone or other matter or thing; or`
  line
  line `(b) takes up, removes, loosens or displaces any rail, sleeper or other matter or things belonging to`
  line `any railway; or`
  line
  line `(c) turns, moves, unlocks or diverts any points or other machinery belonging to any railway; or`
  line
  line `(d) makes or shows, or hides or removes, any signal or light upon or near to any railway; or`
  line
  line `(e) does or causes to be done or attempts to do any other act or thing in relation to any railway,`
  line
  line `with intent or with knowledge that he is likely to endanger the safety of any person travelling on or being`
  line `upon the railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ten years:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, where a person is punishable with rigorous imprisonment, such imprisonment shall`
  line `not be less than--`
  line
  line `(a) three years, in the case of a conviction for the first offence; and`
  line
  line `(b) seven years, in the case of conviction for the second or subsequent offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person unlawfully does any act or thing referred to in any of the clauses of`
  line `sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) with intent to cause the death of any person and the doing of such act or thing causes the death`
  line `of any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) with knowledge that such act or thing is so imminently dangerous that it must in all`
  line `probability cause the death of any person or such bodily injury to any person as is likely to cause the`
  line `death of such person,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with death or imprisonment for life.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (18038)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 179
  title `Damage to or destruction of certain railway properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18038&sectionno=151&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, with intent to`
  line `cause, or knowing that he is likely to cause damage or destruction to any property of a railway referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2), causes by fire, explosive substance or otherwise, damage to such property or`
  line `destruction of such property, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) The properties of a railway referred to in sub-section (1) are railway track, bridges, station`
  line `buildings and installations, carriages or wagons, locomotives, signalling, telecommunications, electric`
  line `traction and block equipments and such other properties as the Central Government being of the opinion`
  line `that damage thereto or destruction thereof is likely to endanger the operation of a railway, may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (18039)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 180
  title `Maliciously hurting or attempting to hurt persons travelling by railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18039&sectionno=152&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `unlawfully throws or causes to fall or strike at against, into or upon any rolling stock forming part of a`
  line `train, any wood, stone or other matter or thing with intent, or with knowledge that he is likely to endanger`
  line `the safety of any person being in or upon such rolling stock or in or upon any other rolling stock forming`
  line `part of the same train, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for life, or with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (18040)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 181
  title `Endangering safety of persons travelling by railway by wilful act or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18040&sectionno=153&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `person by any unlawful act or by any wilful omission or neglect, endangers or causes to be endangered`
  line `the safety of any person travelling on or being upon any railway, or obstructs or causes to be obstructed or`
  line `attempts to obstruct any rolling stock upon any railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (18041)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 182
  title `Endangering safety of persons travelling by railway by rash or negligent act or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18041&sectionno=154&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `If any person in a rash and negligent manner does any act, or omits to do what he is legally bound to do,`
  line `and the act or omission is likely to endanger the safety of any person travelling or being upon any railway,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (18042)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 183
  title `Entering into a compartment reserved or resisting entry into a compartment not reserved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18042&sectionno=155&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any passenger.--`
  line
  line `(a) having entered a compartment wherein no berth or seat has been reserved by a railway`
  line `administration for his use, or`
  line
  line `(b) having unauthorisedly occupied a berth or seat reserved by a railway administration for the`
  line `use of another passenger,`
  line
  line `refuses to leave it when required to do so by any railway servant authorised in this behalf, such railway`
  line `servant may remove him or cause him to be removed, with the aid of any other person, from the`
  line `compartment, berth or seat, as the case may be, and he shall also be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any passenger resists the lawful entry of another passenger into a compartment not reserved for`
  line `the use of the passenger resisting, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (18043)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 184
  title `Travelling on roof, step or engine of a train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18043&sectionno=156&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `If any passenger or any other person, after`
  line `being warned by a railway servant to desist, persists in travelling on the roof, step or footboard of any`
  line `carriage or on an engine, or in any other part of a train not intended for the use of passengers, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees, or with both and may be removed from the railway by any railway servant.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (18044)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 185
  title `Altering or defacing pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18044&sectionno=157&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `If any passenger wilfully alters or defaces his pass or`
  line `ticket so as to render the date, number or any material portion thereof illegible, he shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (18045)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 186
  title `Penalty for contravention of any of the provisions of Chapter XIV.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18045&sectionno=158&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Any person under`
  line `whose authority any railway servant is employed in contravention of any of the provisions of Chapter`
  line `XIV or of the rules made thereunder, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (18046)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 187
  title `Disobedience of drivers or conductors of vehicles to directions of railway servant, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18046&sectionno=159&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line If
  line `any driver or conductor of any vehicle while upon the premises of a railway disobeys the reasonable`
  line `directions of any railway servant or police officer, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (18047)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 188
  title `Opening or breaking a level crossing gate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18047&sectionno=160&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, other than a railway servant or`
  line `a person authorised in this behalf, opens any gate or chain or barrier set up on either side of a level`
  line `crossing which is closed to road traffic, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person breaks any gate or chain or barrier set up on either side of a level crossing which is`
  line `closed to road traffic, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five`
  line years.
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (18048)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 189
  title `Negligently crossing unmanned level crossing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18048&sectionno=161&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `If any person driving or leading a vehicle is`
  line `negligent in crossing an unmanned level crossing, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to one year.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "negligence" in relation to any person driving or`
  line `leading a vehicle in crossing an unmanned level crossing means the crossing of such level crossing by`
  line `such person--`
  line
  line `(a) without stopping or caring to stop the vehicle near such level crossing to observe whether any`
  line `approaching rolling stock is in sight, or`
  line
  line `(b) even while an approaching rolling stock is in sight.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (18049)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 190
  title `Entering carriage or other place reserved for females.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18049&sectionno=162&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `If a male person knowing or having`
  line `reason to believe that a carriage, compartment, berth or seat in a train or room or other place is reserved`
  line `by a railway administration for the exclusive use of females, without lawful excuse,--`
  line
  line `(a) enters such carriage, compartment, room or other place, or having entered such carriage,`
  line `compartment, room or place, remains therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) occupies any such berth or seat having been required by any railway servant to vacate it,`
  line
  line `he shall, in addition to being liable to forfeiture of his pass or ticket, be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees and may also be removed by any railway servant.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (18050)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 191
  title `Giving false account of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18050&sectionno=163&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `If any person required to furnish an account of goods under`
  line `section 66, gives an account which is materially false, he and, if he is not the owner of the goods, the`
  line `owner also shall, without prejudice to his liability to pay any freight or other charge under any provision`
  line `of this Act, be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for every quintal or part`
  line `thereof of such goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (18051)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 192
  title `Unlawfully bringing dangerous goods on a railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18051&sectionno=164&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `If any person, in contravention of`
  line `section 67, takes with him any dangerous goods or entrusts such goods for carriage to the railway`
  line `administration, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees or with both and shall also be liable for any loss,`
  line `injury or damage which may be caused by reason of bringing such goods on the railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (18052)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 193
  title `Unlawfully bringing offensive goods on a railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18052&sectionno=165&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `If any person, in contravention of section`
  line `67, takes with him any offensive goods or entrusts such goods for carriage to the railway administration,`
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and shall also be liable for any`
  line `loss, injury or damage which may be caused by reason of bringing such goods on the railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (18053)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 194
  title `Defacing public notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18053&sectionno=166&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `If any person without lawful authority--`
  line
  line `(a) pulls down or wilfully damages any board or document set up or posted by the order of a`
  line `railway administration on a railway or any rolling stock; or`
  line
  line `(b) obliterates or alters any letters or figures upon any such board or document or upon any`
  line `rolling stock,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (18054)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 195
  title Smoking.
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18054&sectionno=167&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person in any compartment of a train shall, if objected to by any other`
  line `passenger in that compartment, smoke therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a railway administration may prohibit`
  line `smoking in any train or part of a train.`
  line
  line `(3) Whosoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (18055)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 196
  title `Provision with respect to commission of offence by the children of acts endangering safety of person travelling on railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18055&sectionno=168&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person under the age of twelve years is guilty of any of the`
  line `offences under sections 150 to 154, the court convicting him may require the father or guardian of such`
  line `person to execute, within such time as the court may fix, a bond for such amount and for such period as`
  line `the court may direct for the good conduct of such person.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of the bond, if forfeited, shall be recoverable by the court as if it were a fine imposed`
  line `by itself.`
  line
  line `(3) If a father or guardian fails to execute a bond under sub-section (1) within the time fixed by the`
  line `court, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (18056)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 197
  title `Levy of penalty on non-Government railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18056&sectionno=169&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `If a non-Government railway fails to comply`
  line `with, any requisition made, decision or direction given, by the Central Government, under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, or otherwise contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, it shall be open to the`
  line `Central Government, by order, to levy a penalty not exceeding two hundred and fifty rupees and a further`
  line `penalty not exceeding one hundred and fifty rupees for every day during which the contravention`
  line `continues:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be levied except after giving a reasonable opportunity to the`
  line `non-Government railway to make such representation as it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (18057)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 198
  title `Recovery of penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18057&sectionno=170&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Any penalty imposed by the Central Government under section 169,`
  line `shall be recoverable by a suit in the District Court having jurisdiction in the place where the head office of`
  line `the non-Government railway is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (18058)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 199
  title `Section 169 or 170 not to preclude Central Government from taking any other action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18058&sectionno=171&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 169 or 170 shall preclude the Central Government from resorting to any other action to`
  line `compel a non-Government railway to discharge any obligation imposed upon it by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (18059)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 200
  title `Penalty for intoxication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18059&sectionno=172&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant is in a state of intoxication while on duty, he`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and when the performance of any`
  line `duty in such state is likely to endanger the safety of any person travelling on or being upon a railway,`
  line `such railway servant shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (18060)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 201
  title `Abandoning train, etc., without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18060&sectionno=173&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant, when on duty, is entrusted`
  line `with any responsibility connected with the running of a train, or of any other rolling stock from one`
  line `station or place to another station or place, and he abandons his duty before reaching such station or place`
  line `without authority or without properly handing over such train or rolling stock to another authorised`
  line `railway servant, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (18061)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 202
  title `Obstructing running of train, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18061&sectionno=174&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant (whether on duty or otherwise) or`
  line `any other person obstructs or causes to be obstructed or attempts to obstruct any train or other rolling`
  line `stock upon a railway,--`
  line
  line `(a) by squatting or picketing or during any rail roko agitation or bandh; or`
  line
  line `(b) by keeping without authority any rolling stock on the railway; or`
  line
  line `(c) by tampering with, disconnecting or interfering in any other manner with its hose pipe or`
  line `tampering with signal gear or otherwise,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (18062)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 203
  title `Endangering the safety of persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18062&sectionno=175&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant, when on duty, endangers the`
  line `safety of any person--`
  line
  line `(a) by disobeying any rule made under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) by disobeying any instruction, direction or order under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) by any rash or negligent act or omission,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (18063)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 204
  title `Obstructing level crossing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18063&sectionno=176&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant unnecessarily--`
  line
  line `(a) allows any rolling stock to stand across a place where the railway crosses a public road on the`
  line `level; or`
  line
  line `(b) keeps a level crossing closed against the public,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (18064)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 205
  title `False returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18064&sectionno=177&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant required to furnish a return by or under this Act, signs`
  line `and furnishes a return which is false in any material particular or which he knows or believes to be false,`
  line `or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (18065)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 206
  title `Making a false report by a railway servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18065&sectionno=178&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `If any railway servant who is required by a`
  line `railway administration to inquire into a claim for loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery`
  line `of any consignment makes a report which is false or which he knows or believes to be false or does not`
  line `believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (18066)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 207
  title `Arrest for offences under certain sections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 3, for section 179 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18066&sectionno=179&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `^1[179. Arrest for offences under certain sections.-- (1) If any person commits any offence`
  line `mentioned in sections 150 to 152, he may be arrested without warrant or other written authority by any`
  line `railway servant or police officer not below the rank of a head constable.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person commits any offence mentioned in sections 137 to 139, 141 to 147, 153 to 157, 159`
  line `to 167 and 172 to 176, he may be arrested, without warrant or other written authority, by the officer`
  line `authorised by a notified order of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The railway servant or the police officer or the officer authorised, as the case may be, may call to`
  line `his aid any other person to effect the arrest under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person so arrested under this section shall be produced before the nearest Magistrate within a`
  line `period of twenty-four hours of such arrest excluding the time necessary for the journey from the place of`
  line `arrest to the court of the Magistrate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (18067)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 208
  title `Arrest of persons likely to abscond, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18067&sectionno=180&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person who commits any offence under`
  line `this Act, other than an offence mentioned in ^1[sub-section (2) of section 179], or is liable to pay any`
  line `excess charge or other sum demanded under section 138, fails or refuses to give his name and address or`
  line `there is reason to believe that the name and address given by him are fictitious or that he will abscond,`
  line `^2[the officer authorised] may arrest him without warrant or written authority.`
  line
  line `(2) ^3[The officer authorised] may call to his aid any other person to effect the arrest under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Any person arrested under this section shall be produced before the nearest Magistrate within a`
  line `period of twenty-four hours of such arrest excluding the time necessary for the journey from the place of`
  line `arrest to the court of the Magistrate unless he is released earlier on giving bail or if his true name and`
  line `address are ascertained on executing a bond without sureties for his appearance before the Magistrate`
  line `having jurisdiction to try him for the offence.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of Chapter XXIII of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to the giving of bail and the execution of bonds under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "section 179" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for certain words (we.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "The railway servant or the police officer" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_180_a:
  sectionId (18068)
  sectionNo 180A
  orderNo 209
  title `Inquiry by officer authorised to ascertain commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18068&sectionno=180A&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[180A. Inquiry by officer authorised to ascertain commission of offence.-- For ascertaining facts`
  line `and circumstances of a case, the officer authorised may make an inquiry into the commission of an`
  line `offence mentioned in sub-section (2) of section 179 and may file a complaint in the competent court if the`
  line `offence is found to have been committed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_b:
  sectionId (18069)
  sectionNo 180B
  orderNo 210
  title `Powers of officer authorised to inquire.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18069&sectionno=180B&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[180B. Powers of officer authorised to inquire.-- While making an inquiry, the officer authorised`
  line `shall have power to,--`
  line
  line `(i) summon and enforce the attendance of any person and record his statement;`
  line
  line `(ii) require the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(iii) requisition any public record or copy thereof from any office, authority or person;`
  line
  line `(iv) enter and search any premises or person and seize any property or document which may be`
  line `relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_c:
  sectionId (18070)
  sectionNo 180C
  orderNo 211
  title `Disposal of persons arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_c_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18070&sectionno=180C&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[180C. Disposal of persons arrested.--Every person arrested for an offence punishable under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 179 shall, if the arrest was made by a person other than the officer authorised,`
  line `be forwarded, without delay, to such officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_d:
  sectionId (18071)
  sectionNo 180D
  orderNo 212
  title `Inquiry how to be made against arrested person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_d_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18071&sectionno=180D&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[180D. Inquiry how to be made against arrested person.-- (1) When any person is arrested by the`
  line `officer authorised for an offence punishable under this Act, such officer shall proceed to inquire into the`
  line `charge against such person.`
  line
  line `(2) For this purpose, the officer authorised may exercise the same powers and shall be subject to the`
  line `same provisions as the officer in charge of a police station may exercise and is subject to the provisions of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974 ), when investigating a cognizable case:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) if the officer authorised is of the opinion that there is sufficient evidence or reasonable ground`
  line `of suspicion against the accused person, he shall either admit him to bail to appear before a`
  line `Magistrate having jurisdiction in the case, or forward him in custody to such Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) if it appears to the officer authorised that there is not sufficient evidence or reasonable ground`
  line `of suspicion against the accused person, he shall release the accused person on his executing a bond,`
  line `with or without sureties as the officer authorised may direct, to appear, if and when so required,`
  line `before the Magistrate having jurisdiction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_e:
  sectionId (18072)
  sectionNo 180E
  orderNo 213
  title `Search, seizure and arrest how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_e_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18072&sectionno=180E&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[180E. Search, seizure and arrest how to be made.-- All searches, seizures and arrests made under`
  line `this Act shall be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974 ), relating respectively to searches and arrests made under that Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_f:
  sectionId (18073)
  sectionNo 180F
  orderNo 214
  title `Cognizance by Court on a complaint made by officer authorised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_f_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18073&sectionno=180F&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[180F. Cognizance by Court on a complaint made by officer authorised.-- No court shall take`
  line `cognizance of an offence mentioned in sub-section (2) of section 179 except on a complaint made by the`
  line `officer authorised.]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_g:
  sectionId (18074)
  sectionNo 180G
  orderNo 215
  title `Punishment for certain offences in relation to inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_g_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 51 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18074&sectionno=180G&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_180_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[180G. Punishment for certain offences in relation to inquiry. --Whoever intentionally insults or`
  line `causes any interruption in the inquiry proceedings or deliberately makes a false statement before the`
  line `inquiring officer shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (18075)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 216
  title `Magistrate having jurisdiction under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18075&sectionno=181&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (18076)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 217
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18076&sectionno=182&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person committing an offence under this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder shall be triable for such offence in any place in which he may be or which the State`
  line `Government may notify in this behalf, as well as in any other place in which he is liable to be tried under`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall be published in the Official Gazette, and a copy`
  line `thereof shall be exhibited for the information of the public in some conspicuous place at such railway`
  line `stations as the State Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (18077)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 218
  title `Power to provide other transport services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18077&sectionno=183&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway administration may, for the`
  line `purpose of facilitating the carriage of passengers or goods or to provide integrated service for such`
  line `carriage, provide any other mode of transport.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply to the carriage of passengers or goods by the mode of transport referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (18078)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 219
  title `Taxation on railways by local authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18078&sectionno=184&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law, a railway administration shall not be liable to pay any tax in aid of the funds`
  line `of any local authority unless the Central Government, by notification, declares the railway administration`
  line `to be liable to pay the tax specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) While a notification of the Central Government under sub-section (1) is in force, the railway`
  line `administration shall be liable to pay to the local authority either the tax specified in the notification or, in`
  line `lieu thereof, such sum, if any, as an officer appointed in this behalf by the Central Government may,`
  line `having regard to all the circumstances of the case, from time to time, determine to be fair and reasonable.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may at any time revoke or vary a notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prevent any railway administration from entering into`
  line `a contract with any local authority for the supply of water or light, or for the scavenging of railway`
  line `premises, or for any other service which the local authority may be rendering or be prepared to render to`
  line `the railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (18079)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 220
  title `Taxation on railways for advertisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18079&sectionno=185&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law, a railway administration shall not be liable to pay any tax to any local`
  line `authority in respect of any advertisement made on any part of the railway unless the Central Government,`
  line `by notification, declares the railway administration to be liable to pay the tax specified in such`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may at any time revoke or vary a notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (18080)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 221
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18080&sectionno=186&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, any railway administration, a railway servant or any other person for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rules or orders`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (18081)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 222
  title `Restriction on execution against railway property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18081&sectionno=187&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `(1) No rolling stock, machinery, plant,`
  line `tools, fittings, materials or effects used or provided by a railway administration for the purpose of traffic`
  line `on its railway, or of its stations or workshops, shall be liable to be taken in execution of any decree or`
  line `order of any court or of any local authority or person having by law the power to attach or distrain`
  line `property or otherwise to cause property to be taken in execution, without the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be construed to affect the authority of any court to attach the`
  line `earnings of a railway in execution of a decree or order.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (18082)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 223
  title `Railway servants to be public servants for the purposes of Chapter IX and section 409 of the Indian Penal Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18082&sectionno=188&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any railway servant, who is not a public servant within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall be deemed to be a public servant for`
  line `the purposes of Chapter IX and section 409 of that Code.`
  line
  line `(2) In the definition of legal remuneration in section 161 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the`
  line `word Government shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), be deemed to include any employer of a`
  line `railway servant as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (18083)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 224
  title `Railway servants not to engage in trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18083&sectionno=189&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `A railway servant shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) purchase or bid for, either in person or by an agent, in his own name or in that of another, or`
  line `jointly or in shares with others, any property put to auction under section 83 or section 84 or section`
  line `85 or section 90; or`
  line
  line `(b) in contravention of any direction of the railway administration in this behalf, engage in trade.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (18084)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 225
  title `Procedure for delivery to railway administration of property detained by a railway servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18084&sectionno=190&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `If a railway servant is discharged from service or is suspended, or dies or absconds or absents`
  line `himself, and he or his wife or widow or any member of his family or his representative, refuses or`
  line `neglects, after notice in writing for that purpose, to deliver up to the railway administration or to a person`
  line `appointed by the railway administration, in this behalf, any station, office or other building with its`
  line `appurtenances, or any books, papers, keys, equipment or other matters, belonging to the railway`
  line `administration and in the possession or custody of such railway servant at the occurrence of any such`
  line `event as aforesaid, any Metropolitan Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class may, on`
  line `application made by or on behalf of the railway administration, order any police officer, with proper`
  line `assistance, to enter upon the station, office or other building and remove any person found therein and`
  line `take possession thereof, or to take possession of the books, papers or other matters, and to deliver the`
  line `same to the railway administration or to a person appointed by the railway administration in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (18085)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 226
  title `Proof of entries in records and documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18085&sectionno=191&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `Entries made in the records or other documents`
  line `of a railway administration shall be admitted in evidence in all proceedings by or against the railway`
  line `administration, and all such entries may be proved either by the production of the records or other`
  line `documents of the railway administration containing such entries or by the production of a copy of the`
  line `entries certified by the officer having custody of the records or other documents under his signature and`
  line `stating that it is a true copy of the original entries and that such original entries are contained in the`
  line `records or other documents of the railway administration in his possession.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (18086)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 227
  title `Service of notice, etc., on railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18086&sectionno=192&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `Any notice or other document required or`
  line `authorised by this Act to be served on a railway administration may be served, in the case of a Zonal`
  line `Railway, on the General Manager or any of the railway servant authorised by the General Manager, and`
  line `in the case of any other railway, on the owner or lessee of the railway or the person working the railway`
  line `under an agreement--`
  line
  line `(a) by delivering it to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) by leaving it at his office; or`
  line
  line `(c) by registered post to his office address.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (18087)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 228
  title `Service of notice, etc., by railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18087&sectionno=193&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise provided in this Act or`
  line `the rules framed thereunder, any notice or other document required or authorised by this Act to be served`
  line `on any person by a railway administration may be served--`
  line
  line `(a) by delivering it to the person; or`
  line
  line `(b) by leaving it at the usual or last known place of abode of the person; or`
  line
  line `(c) by registered post addressed to the person at his usual or last known place of abode.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (18088)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 229
  title `Presumption where notice is served by post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18088&sectionno=194&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `Where a notice or other document is served by`
  line `post, it shall be deemed to have been served at the time when the letter containing it would be delivered in`
  line `the ordinary course of post, and in proving such service, it shall be sufficient to prove that the letter`
  line `containing the notice or other document was property addressed and registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (18089)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 230
  title `Representation of railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18089&sectionno=195&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) A railway administration may, by order in`
  line `writing, authorise any railway servant or other person to act for, or represent it, as the case may be, in any`
  line `proceeding before any civil, criminal or other court..`
  line
  line `(2) A person authorised by a railway administration to conduct prosecutions on its behalf shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in section 302 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be entitled`
  line `to conduct such prosecutions without the permission of the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (18090)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 231
  title `Power to exempt railway from Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18090&sectionno=196&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `exempt any railway from all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid as soon as may be after it is issued`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (18091)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 232
  title `Matters supplemental to the definitions of "railway" and "railway servant".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18091&sectionno=197&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purposes of sections 67, 113, 121, 123, 147, 151 to 154, 160, 164, 166, 168, 170, 171, 173 to 176, 179,`
  line `180, 182, 184, 185, 187 to 190, 192, 193, 195 and of this section, the word "railway" whether it occurs`
  line `alone or as a prefix to another word, has reference to a railway or portion of a railway under construction`
  line `and to a railway or portion of a railway not used for the public carriage of passengers, animals or goods as`
  line `well as to a railway falling within the definition of that word in clause (31) of section 2.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sections 7, 24, 113, 146, 172 to 176 and 188 to 190, the expression "railway`
  line `servant" includes a person employed under a railway in connection with the service thereof by a person`
  line `fulfilling a contract with the railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (18092)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 233
  title `General power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18092&sectionno=198&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any power to make rules contained`
  line `elsewhere in this Act, the Central Government may make rules generally to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (18093)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 234
  title `Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18093&sectionno=199&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the`
  line `rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (18094)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 235
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596&sectionId=18094&sectionno=200&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00003_198924_1517807322596
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890) (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as the repealed Act)--`
  line
  line `(a) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken (including any`
  line `rule, notification, inspection, order or notice made or issued, or any appointment or declaration made`
  line `or any licence, permission, authorisation or exemption granted or any document or instrument`
  line `executed or any direction given or any proceedings taken or any penalty or fine imposed) under the`
  line `repealed Act shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have`
  line `been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any complaint made to the Railway Rates Tribunal under sub-section (1) of section 41 of the`
  line `repealed Act but not disposed of before the commencement of this Act and any complaint that may`
  line `be made to the said Tribunal against any act or omission of a railway administration under the`
  line `repealed Act shall be heard and decided by the Tribunal constituted under this Act in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of Chapter VII of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of`
  line repeal.
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
